190
00:12:08,479 --> 00:12:09,480
<font color="#ffff80">Right away, sir.</font>

191
00:12:09,605 --> 00:12:10,606
<font color="#ffff80">Hold it.</font>

192
00:12:12,858 --> 00:12:14,652
<font color="#ffff80">Who are you?</font>

193
00:12:14,777 --> 00:12:16,529
<font color="#ffff80">I'm Zero, sir. The
new Lobby Boy.</font>

194
00:12:16,737 --> 00:12:17,947
<font color="#ffff80">Zero, you say? Yes, sir.</font>

195
00:12:18,030 --> 00:12:19,406
<font color="#ffff80">I've never heard of you,
never laid eyes on you.</font>

196
00:12:19,490 --> 00:12:20,491
<font color="#ffff80">Who hired you?</font>

197
00:12:20,699 --> 00:12:21,825
<font color="#ffff80">Mr. Mosher, sir.</font>

198
00:12:21,992 --> 00:12:23,118
<font color="#ffff80">Mr. Mosher!</font>

199
00:12:24,411 --> 00:12:25,454
<font color="#ffff80">Yes, Monsieur Gustave?</font>

200
00:12:25,663 --> 00:12:28,290
<font color="#ffff80">Am I to understand you've
surreptitiously hired this young man</font>

201
00:12:28,374 --> 00:12:29,667
<font color="#ffff80">in the position of a Lobby Boy?</font>

202
00:12:29,875 --> 00:12:31,627
<font color="#ffff80">He's been engaged
for a trial period,</font>

203
00:12:31,752 --> 00:12:33,462
<font color="#ffff80">pending your
approval, of course.</font>

204
00:12:33,546 --> 00:12:34,838
<font color="#ffff80">Uh...</font>

205
00:12:34,964 --> 00:12:37,341
<font color="#ffff80">Perhaps, yes. Thank you, Mr.
Mosher.</font>

206
00:12:37,466 --> 00:12:39,802
<font color="#ffff80">You're most welcome,
Monsieur Gustave.</font>

207
00:12:40,386 --> 00:12:42,680
<font color="#ffff80">You're now going to be
officially interviewed.</font>

208
00:12:42,888 --> 00:12:45,057
<font color="#ffff80">Should I go and light
the candle first, sir?</font>

209
00:12:45,266 --> 00:12:46,517
<font color="#ffff80">What? No.</font>

210
00:12:50,271 --> 00:12:51,313
<font color="#ffff80">Experience?</font>

211
00:12:51,522 --> 00:12:53,649
<font color="#ffff80">Hotel Kinski, Kitchen
Boy, six months.</font>

212
00:12:53,857 --> 00:12:56,026
<font color="#ffff80">Hotel Berlitz, Mop and
Broom Boy, three months.</font>

213
00:12:56,235 --> 00:12:57,570
<font color="#ffff80">Before that I was a
Skillet Scrubber...</font>

214
00:12:57,695 --> 00:12:59,029
<font color="#ffff80">Experience, zero.</font>

215
00:12:59,113 --> 00:13:00,114
<font color="#ffff80">Thank you again,
Monsieur Gustave.</font>

216
00:13:00,197 --> 00:13:01,198
<font color="#ffff80">Straighten that cap, Anatole.</font>

217
00:13:01,282 --> 00:13:03,158
<font color="#ffff80">The pleasure's mine, <i>Herr</i> Schneider.
The strap's busted.</font>

218
00:13:03,242 --> 00:13:05,119
<font color="#ffff80">These are not acceptable.
I fully agree.</font>

219
00:13:05,202 --> 00:13:06,537
<font color="#ffff80">Education?</font>

220
00:13:06,662 --> 00:13:07,913
<font color="#ffff80">I studied reading and spelling.</font>

221
00:13:08,122 --> 00:13:10,374
<font color="#ffff80">I started my primary school.
I almost...</font>

222
00:13:10,583 --> 00:13:11,584
<font color="#ffff80">Education, zero.</font>

223
00:13:11,709 --> 00:13:12,751
<font color="#ffff80">Now it's exploded.</font>

224
00:13:12,876 --> 00:13:15,004
<font color="#ffff80">Good morning, Cicero.
Call the goddamn plumber!</font>

225
00:13:15,087 --> 00:13:16,213
<font color="#ffff80">This afternoon,
Monsieur Gustave?</font>

226
00:13:16,380 --> 00:13:17,506
<font color="#ffff80">Without fail, Frau Liebling.</font>

227
00:13:17,590 --> 00:13:19,174
<font color="#ffff80">What in hell is this? Not now.</font>

228
00:13:19,341 --> 00:13:21,343
<font color="#ffff80">Family?</font>

229
00:13:23,762 --> 00:13:25,598
<font color="#ffff80">Zero.</font>

230
00:13:25,806 --> 00:13:27,808
<font color="#ffff80">Six, Igor.</font>

231
00:13:35,232 --> 00:13:37,067
<font color="#ffff80">Why do you want to
be a Lobby Boy?</font>

232
00:13:39,069 --> 00:13:43,532
<font color="#ffff80">Well, who wouldn't, at
the Grand Budapest, sir?</font>

233
00:13:43,741 --> 00:13:45,743
<font color="#ffff80">It's an institution.</font>

234
00:13:48,621 --> 00:13:50,205
<font color="#ffff80">Very good.</font>

235
00:14:05,471 --> 00:14:06,513
<font color="#ffff80">A thousand Klubecks.</font>

236
00:14:06,639 --> 00:14:07,681
<font color="#ffff80">My goodness.</font>

237
00:14:08,974 --> 00:14:11,727
<font color="#ffff80">Were you ever a Lobby Boy, sir?</font>

238
00:14:11,935 --> 00:14:12,936
<font color="#ffff80">What do you think?</font>

239
00:14:13,145 --> 00:14:15,064
<font color="#ffff80">Well, I suppose you'd have
to start somewhere...</font>

240
00:14:15,272 --> 00:14:16,940
<font color="#ffff80">Go and light the goddamn candle.
Yes, sir.</font>

241
00:14:22,154 --> 00:14:24,156
<font color="#ffff80"><i>MR. MOUSTAFA: And
so, my life began.</i></font>

242
00:14:26,992 --> 00:14:28,285
<font color="#ffff80"><i>Junior Lobby Boy in-training,</i></font>

243
00:14:28,494 --> 00:14:29,912
<font color="#ffff80"><i>Grand Budapest Hotel,</i></font>

244
00:14:30,120 --> 00:14:33,290
<font color="#ffff80"><i>under the strict command
of Monsieur Gustave H.</i></font>

245
00:14:33,499 --> 00:14:36,627
<font color="#ffff80"><i>I became his pupil, and he was
to be my counselor and guardian.</i></font>

246
00:14:36,835 --> 00:14:38,545
<font color="#ffff80"><i>GUSTAVE H: What is</i> a <i>Lobby Boy?</i></font>

247
00:14:38,754 --> 00:14:42,132
<font color="#ffff80"><i>A Lobby Boy's completely
invisible, yet always in sight.</i></font>

248
00:14:42,383 --> 00:14:44,385
<font color="#ffff80"><i>A Lobby Boy remembers
what people hate.</i></font>

249
00:14:44,593 --> 00:14:46,387
<font color="#ffff80"><i>A Lobby Boy anticipates
the client's needs</i></font>

250
00:14:46,595 --> 00:14:48,680
<font color="#ffff80"><i>before the needs are needed.</i></font>

251
00:14:48,889 --> 00:14:51,975
<font color="#ffff80"><i>A Lobby Boy is, above
all, discreet to a fault.</i></font>

252
00:14:52,184 --> 00:14:54,269
<font color="#ffff80">Our guests know their
deepest secrets,</font>

253
00:14:54,353 --> 00:14:55,938
<font color="#ffff80">some of which are,
frankly, rather unseemly,</font>

254
00:14:56,021 --> 00:14:57,856
<font color="#ffff80">will go with us to our graves.</font>

255
00:14:58,065 --> 00:14:59,316
<font color="#ffff80">So keep your mouth shut, Zero.</font>

256
00:14:59,441 --> 00:15:00,692
<font color="#ffff80">Yes, sir.</font>

257
00:15:02,820 --> 00:15:04,780
<font color="#ffff80">That's all for now.</font>

258
00:15:04,988 --> 00:15:06,907
<font color="#ffff80"><i>MR. MOUSTAFA: I began to realize
that many of the hotel's</i></font>

259
00:15:07,116 --> 00:15:10,828
<font color="#ffff80"><i>most valued and distinguished
guests came for him.</i></font>

260
00:15:11,036 --> 00:15:12,663
<font color="#ffff80"><i>It seemed to be an essential
part of his duties...</i></font>

261
00:15:12,746 --> 00:15:14,081
<font color="#ffff80">Ah!</font>

262
00:15:14,164 --> 00:15:16,417
<font color="#ffff80"><i>...but I believe it was
also his pleasure.</i></font>

263
00:15:18,502 --> 00:15:20,462
<font color="#ffff80"><i>The requirements were
always the same.</i></font>

264
00:15:20,671 --> 00:15:23,132
<font color="#ffff80"><i>They had to be rich,</i></font>

265
00:15:23,340 --> 00:15:24,425
<font color="#ffff80"><i>old,</i></font>

266
00:15:24,633 --> 00:15:25,801
<font color="#ffff80">insecure,</font>

267
00:15:26,009 --> 00:15:27,052
<font color="#ffff80"><i>vain,</i></font>

268
00:15:27,261 --> 00:15:28,512
<font color="#ffff80"><i>superficial,</i></font>

269
00:15:28,720 --> 00:15:29,805
<font color="#ffff80"><i>blonde,</i></font>

270
00:15:30,013 --> 00:15:31,515
<font color="#ffff80">needy.</font>

271
00:15:32,724 --> 00:15:34,726
<font color="#ffff80">Why blonde?</font>

272
00:15:36,854 --> 00:15:38,147
<font color="#ffff80">Because they all were.</font>

273
00:15:38,439 --> 00:15:39,731
<font color="#ffff80"><i>He was, by the way,</i></font>

274
00:15:39,940 --> 00:15:43,527
<font color="#ffff80"><i>the most liberally perfumed
man I had ever encountered.</i></font>

275
00:15:43,735 --> 00:15:46,572
<font color="#ffff80"><i>The scent announced his
approach from a great distance</i></font>

276
00:15:48,073 --> 00:15:50,576
<font color="#ffff80"><i>and lingered for many
minutes after he was gone.</i></font>

277
00:15:52,661 --> 00:15:55,456
<font color="#ffff80"><i>I worked six days each week
plus a half-day Sunday,</i></font>

278
00:15:55,664 --> 00:15:57,916
<font color="#ffff80"><i>5:00 AM until just
after midnight.</i></font>

279
00:15:59,084 --> 00:16:01,670
<font color="#ffff80"><i>Our meals were small but
frequent, for stamina.</i></font>

280
00:16:01,879 --> 00:16:04,673
<font color="#ffff80"><i>Two breakfasts, two lunches
and a late supper.</i></font>

281
00:16:05,841 --> 00:16:09,094
<font color="#ffff80"><i>Monsieur Gustave also
delivered</i> a <i>nightly sermon.</i></font>

282
00:16:09,303 --> 00:16:12,389
<font color="#ffff80">Rudeness is merely the
expression of fear.</font>

283
00:16:12,598 --> 00:16:14,808
<font color="#ffff80">People fear they won't
get what they want.</font>

284
00:16:15,017 --> 00:16:18,520
<font color="#ffff80">The most dreadful and unattractive
person only needs to be loved,</font>

285
00:16:18,729 --> 00:16:21,148
<font color="#ffff80">and they will open
up like a flower.</font>

286
00:16:21,356 --> 00:16:22,941
<font color="#ffff80">I am reminded of a verse,</font>

287
00:16:23,150 --> 00:16:25,569
<font color="#ffff80">"The painter's brush
touched the inchoate face</font>

288
00:16:25,777 --> 00:16:27,738
<font color="#ffff80">"by ends of nimble bristles</font>

289
00:16:27,946 --> 00:16:29,823
<font color="#ffff80">"and with their blush
of first color,</font>

290
00:16:29,948 --> 00:16:31,825
<font color="#ffff80">"rendered her lifeless
cheek living."</font>

291
00:16:32,034 --> 00:16:35,078
<font color="#ffff80"><i>MR. MOUSTAFA: His own dinner,
he took alone in his room.</i></font>

292
00:16:40,792 --> 00:16:44,463
<font color="#ffff80"><i>The identity of the owner of the
hotel was unknown to all of us.</i></font>

293
00:16:44,671 --> 00:16:48,467
<font color="#ffff80"><i>Each month, his emissary, known
as Deputy Kovacs, arrived</i></font>

294
00:16:48,675 --> 00:16:50,511
<font color="#ffff80"><i>to review the books
and convey messages</i></font>

295
00:16:50,719 --> 00:16:53,222
<font color="#ffff80"><i>on behalf of the
mysterious proprietor.</i></font>

296
00:16:53,430 --> 00:16:56,391
<font color="#ffff80"><i>On these occasions, Monsieur
Gustave and our business manager,</i></font>

297
00:16:56,600 --> 00:17:00,103
<font color="#ffff80"><i>Herr Becker, met with him in private
consultation above Reception.</i></font>

298
00:17:12,908 --> 00:17:15,369
<font color="#ffff80"><i>This was also when I met Agatha,</i></font>

299
00:17:33,554 --> 00:17:35,556
<font color="#ffff80"><i>but we won't discuss that.</i></font>

300
00:18:26,481 --> 00:18:27,482
<font color="#ffff80">What do you want? Look.</font>

301
00:18:32,571 --> 00:18:33,739
<font color="#ffff80">GUSTAVE H: Dear God.</font>

302
00:18:34,031 --> 00:18:35,198
<font color="#ffff80">I'm terribly sorry, sir.</font>

303
00:18:35,407 --> 00:18:36,408
<font color="#ffff80">We must go to her.</font>

304
00:18:36,491 --> 00:18:37,492
<font color="#ffff80">We must?</font>

305
00:18:37,618 --> 00:18:39,328
<font color="#ffff80">Tout de suite. She
needs me, and I need</font>

306
00:18:39,453 --> 00:18:41,163
<font color="#ffff80">you to help me with
my bags and so on.</font>

307
00:18:43,123 --> 00:18:44,833
<font color="#ffff80">How fast can you pack?
Five minutes.</font>

308
00:18:45,042 --> 00:18:47,002
<font color="#ffff80">Do it. And bring a bottle
of the Pouilly-Jouvet '26</font>

309
00:18:47,085 --> 00:18:48,295
<font color="#ffff80">in an ice bucket
with two glasses</font>

310
00:18:48,378 --> 00:18:51,340
<font color="#ffff80">so we don't have to drink the cat
piss they serve in the dining car.</font>

311
00:19:00,390 --> 00:19:02,517
<font color="#ffff80">I blame myself.</font>

312
00:19:03,268 --> 00:19:06,563
<font color="#ffff80">She tried to tell me she had a premonition.
I didn't listen.</font>

313
00:19:06,772 --> 00:19:08,357
<font color="#ffff80">All of Lutz will be
dressed in black,</font>

314
00:19:08,440 --> 00:19:10,484
<font color="#ffff80">except her own ghastly,
deceitful children</font>

315
00:19:10,567 --> 00:19:12,736
<font color="#ffff80">whom she loathed and
couldn't bear to kiss hello.</font>

316
00:19:12,944 --> 00:19:15,238
<font color="#ffff80">They'll be dancing like gypsies.</font>

317
00:19:18,241 --> 00:19:20,327
<font color="#ffff80">There's really no point in
doing anything in life,</font>

318
00:19:20,410 --> 00:19:22,287
<font color="#ffff80">because it's all over in
the blink of an eye...</font>

319
00:19:22,412 --> 00:19:25,374
<font color="#ffff80">And, the next thing you
know, rigor mortis sets in.</font>

320
00:19:25,582 --> 00:19:28,418
<font color="#ffff80">Oh, how the good die young.</font>

321
00:19:28,627 --> 00:19:31,588
<font color="#ffff80">With any luck, she's left a few
Klubecks for your old friend,</font>

322
00:19:31,755 --> 00:19:33,340
<font color="#ffff80">but one never knows
until the ink</font>

323
00:19:33,465 --> 00:19:35,050
<font color="#ffff80">is dry on the death certificate.</font>

324
00:19:36,551 --> 00:19:38,387
<font color="#ffff80">She was dynamite in
the sack, by the way.</font>

325
00:19:40,430 --> 00:19:42,766
<font color="#ffff80"><i>She was 84, Monsieur Gustave.</i></font>

326
00:19:42,933 --> 00:19:44,434
<font color="#ffff80">I've had older.</font>

327
00:19:44,601 --> 00:19:46,228
<font color="#ffff80">When you're young,
it's all fillet steak,</font>

328
00:19:46,436 --> 00:19:49,439
<font color="#ffff80">but as the years go by, you have
to move on to the cheaper cuts,</font>

329
00:19:49,606 --> 00:19:51,900
<font color="#ffff80">which is fine with me,
because I like those.</font>

330
00:19:52,109 --> 00:19:54,361
<font color="#ffff80">More flavorful, or so they say.</font>

331
00:19:57,739 --> 00:19:59,741
<font color="#ffff80">Why are we stopping
at a barley field?</font>

332
00:20:14,965 --> 00:20:16,675
<font color="#ffff80">Well, hello there, chaps.</font>

333
00:20:16,967 --> 00:20:18,301
<font color="#ffff80">Documents, please.</font>

334
00:20:18,510 --> 00:20:20,512
<font color="#ffff80">With pleasure.</font>

335
00:20:24,599 --> 00:20:26,476
<font color="#ffff80">It's not a very flattering
portrait, I'm afraid.</font>

336
00:20:26,685 --> 00:20:28,311
<font color="#ffff80">I was once considered
a great beauty.</font>

337
00:20:29,646 --> 00:20:31,982
<font color="#ffff80">What does the "F" stand for?
Fritz? Franz?</font>

338
00:20:32,190 --> 00:20:33,442
<font color="#ffff80">Franz.</font>

339
00:20:33,567 --> 00:20:34,776
<font color="#ffff80">I knew it!</font>

340
00:20:36,153 --> 00:20:38,029
<font color="#ffff80">He's making a funny face.</font>

341
00:20:38,280 --> 00:20:41,825
<font color="#ffff80">That's a Migratory Visa with Stage
Three Worker Status, Franz, darling.</font>

342
00:20:41,992 --> 00:20:44,119
<font color="#ffff80">He's with me.</font>

343
00:20:44,953 --> 00:20:45,996
<font color="#ffff80">Come outside, please.</font>

344
00:20:47,497 --> 00:20:50,459
<font color="#ffff80">Now, wait a minute. Sit down, Zero.
His papers are in order.</font>

345
00:20:50,667 --> 00:20:52,127
<font color="#ffff80">I cross-referenced
them myself with</font>

346
00:20:52,252 --> 00:20:53,670
<font color="#ffff80">the Bureau of Labor
and Servitude.</font>

347
00:20:53,879 --> 00:20:55,714
<font color="#ffff80">You can't arrest him simply
because he's a bloody immigrant.</font>

348
00:20:55,839 --> 00:20:58,008
<font color="#ffff80">He hasn't done anything wrong.</font>

349
00:21:03,638 --> 00:21:05,557
<font color="#ffff80">Stop it, damn you!</font>

350
00:21:05,807 --> 00:21:07,851
<font color="#ffff80">Never mind, Monsieur Gustave!
Let them proceed!</font>

351
00:21:08,059 --> 00:21:09,686
<font color="#ffff80">GUSTAVE H: Ow! That hurts!</font>

352
00:21:12,522 --> 00:21:15,317
<font color="#ffff80">You filthy, goddamn,
pock-marked, fascist assholes!</font>

353
00:21:15,525 --> 00:21:17,819
<font color="#ffff80">Take your hands
off my Lobby Boy!</font>

354
00:21:29,706 --> 00:21:31,041
<font color="#ffff80">What's the problem?</font>

355
00:21:31,208 --> 00:21:32,292
<font color="#ffff80">This is outrageous.</font>

356
00:21:32,375 --> 00:21:35,045
<font color="#ffff80">The young man works for me at the
Grand Budapest Hotel in Nebelsbad.</font>

357
00:21:37,047 --> 00:21:38,381
<font color="#ffff80"><i>Monsieur Gustave?</i></font>

358
00:21:41,218 --> 00:21:43,220
<font color="#ffff80">My name is Henckels.</font>

359
00:21:44,554 --> 00:21:47,599
<font color="#ffff80">I'm the son of Dr. and Mrs.
Wolfgang Henckels-Bergersdörfer.</font>

360
00:21:47,849 --> 00:21:49,559
<font color="#ffff80">Do you remember me?</font>

361
00:21:50,560 --> 00:21:54,231
<font color="#ffff80">I know exactly who you are. It's uncanny.
You're little Albert.</font>

362
00:21:54,397 --> 00:21:56,233
<font color="#ffff80">I'm terribly embarrassed.
Release them.</font>

363
00:21:57,108 --> 00:21:59,236
<font color="#ffff80">Release them.</font>

364
00:22:04,241 --> 00:22:05,242
<font color="#ffff80">Hmm.</font>

365
00:22:06,034 --> 00:22:07,285
<font color="#ffff80">Your colleague is stateless.</font>

366
00:22:07,536 --> 00:22:09,746
<font color="#ffff80">He'll need to apply for a
revised Special Transit Permit,</font>

367
00:22:09,955 --> 00:22:13,250
<font color="#ffff80">which at this point may be
very difficult to acquire.</font>

368
00:22:13,416 --> 00:22:14,417
<font color="#ffff80">Take this.</font>

369
00:22:16,086 --> 00:22:17,462
<font color="#ffff80">It's temporary</font>

370
00:22:17,546 --> 00:22:18,964
<font color="#ffff80">but it's the best I can
offer, I'm afraid.</font>

371
00:22:19,047 --> 00:22:21,216
<font color="#ffff80">And how's your wonderful mother?</font>

372
00:22:21,424 --> 00:22:23,343
<font color="#ffff80">She's very well, thank you.
I adore her.</font>

373
00:22:23,426 --> 00:22:25,720
<font color="#ffff80">Send my love. I will.</font>

374
00:22:26,638 --> 00:22:28,473
<font color="#ffff80">Your companion was
very kind to me</font>

375
00:22:28,598 --> 00:22:30,475
<font color="#ffff80">when I was a lonely little boy.</font>

376
00:22:31,560 --> 00:22:33,979
<font color="#ffff80">My men and I apologize
for disturbing you.</font>

