00:35:29,170 --> 00:35:30,880
<font color="#ffff80">"I hereby place you under
arrest for the murder</font>

567
00:35:31,088 --> 00:35:33,549
<font color="#ffff80">"of Madame Céline Villeneuve
Desgoffe und Taxis."</font>

568
00:35:33,716 --> 00:35:35,217
<font color="#ffff80">I knew there was
something fishy.</font>

569
00:35:35,342 --> 00:35:36,844
<font color="#ffff80">We never got the cause of death.</font>

570
00:35:37,052 --> 00:35:40,222
<font color="#ffff80">She's been murdered and
you think I did it.</font>

571
00:35:41,891 --> 00:35:43,893
<font color="#ffff80">HENCKELS: Hey!</font>

572
00:35:45,728 --> 00:35:47,730
<font color="#ffff80">Stop!</font>

573
00:36:36,904 --> 00:36:38,948
<font color="#ffff80">What happened?</font>

574
00:36:39,156 --> 00:36:41,617
<font color="#ffff80">What happened, my dear Zero,
is I beat the living shit</font>

575
00:36:41,784 --> 00:36:44,453
<font color="#ffff80">out of a sniveling little
runt called Pinky Bandinski</font>

576
00:36:44,662 --> 00:36:46,455
<font color="#ffff80">who had the gall to
question my virility,</font>

577
00:36:46,622 --> 00:36:48,916
<font color="#ffff80">because if there's one thing we've
learned from penny dreadfuls,</font>

578
00:36:49,124 --> 00:36:51,126
<font color="#ffff80">it's that, when you find
yourself in a place like this,</font>

579
00:36:51,335 --> 00:36:52,795
<font color="#ffff80">you must never be a candy-ass.</font>

580
00:36:53,003 --> 00:36:54,964
<font color="#ffff80">You've got to prove
yourself from Day One.</font>

581
00:36:55,130 --> 00:36:56,632
<font color="#ffff80">You've got to win their respect.</font>

582
00:36:56,966 --> 00:37:00,094
<font color="#ffff80">You should take a long look
at his ugly mug this morning.</font>

583
00:37:03,430 --> 00:37:05,266
<font color="#ffff80">He's, actually,
become a dear friend.</font>

584
00:37:05,474 --> 00:37:06,976
<font color="#ffff80">You'll meet him, I hope.</font>

585
00:37:07,977 --> 00:37:10,020
<font color="#ffff80">So. You've talked to Kovacs?</font>

586
00:37:10,271 --> 00:37:11,647
<font color="#ffff80">I saw him last night in secret.</font>

587
00:37:11,855 --> 00:37:14,024
<font color="#ffff80">He made me take an oath on a
Bible I wouldn't tell a soul.</font>

588
00:37:14,275 --> 00:37:15,359
<font color="#ffff80">You're supposed to also.</font>

589
00:37:15,484 --> 00:37:16,652
<font color="#ffff80">I'll do that later.</font>

590
00:37:16,819 --> 00:37:17,987
<font color="#ffff80">He suspects you're innocent.</font>

591
00:37:18,153 --> 00:37:19,321
<font color="#ffff80">Of course he does.</font>

592
00:37:19,488 --> 00:37:21,282
<font color="#ffff80">What's the charge?</font>

593
00:37:22,700 --> 00:37:25,661
<font color="#ffff80">In the small hours of the
evening of 19 October,</font>

594
00:37:25,869 --> 00:37:28,914
<font color="#ffff80">an individual well-known to the house
and staff, a Monsieur Gustave H,</font>

595
00:37:29,123 --> 00:37:32,251
<font color="#ffff80">did arrive at the Desgoffe
und Taxis residence in Lutz</font>

596
00:37:32,459 --> 00:37:34,962
<font color="#ffff80">and entered by the
rear service alley,</font>

597
00:37:35,170 --> 00:37:36,505
<font color="#ffff80">alerting no one to his presence,</font>

598
00:37:36,714 --> 00:37:40,467
<font color="#ffff80">and did then proceed by way of
back stairs and servants' passage,</font>

599
00:37:40,676 --> 00:37:43,012
<font color="#ffff80">to deliver himself into the
private chambers of Madame D.</font>

600
00:37:43,220 --> 00:37:45,764
<font color="#ffff80">There is no evidence to
indicate whether this visit</font>

601
00:37:45,973 --> 00:37:48,434
<font color="#ffff80">had been pre-arranged
with her or not.</font>

602
00:37:48,642 --> 00:37:53,522
<font color="#ffff80">The next morning Madame D was found
dead by strychnine poisoning.</font>

603
00:37:53,731 --> 00:37:55,858
<font color="#ffff80">Monsieur Gustave was not
observed on the premises again</font>

604
00:37:56,066 --> 00:37:59,236
<font color="#ffff80">until, of course,
24 hours later.</font>

605
00:37:59,445 --> 00:38:01,697
<font color="#ffff80">The identity of his
accusers is made</font>

606
00:38:01,864 --> 00:38:04,116
<font color="#ffff80">clear in this
notarized deposition.</font>

607
00:38:04,325 --> 00:38:07,745
<font color="#ffff80">They include, essentially, all
members of the extended family,</font>

608
00:38:07,953 --> 00:38:12,666
<font color="#ffff80">but the key witness who actually
ostensibly saw the alleged events</font>

609
00:38:12,875 --> 00:38:15,502
<font color="#ffff80">appears to have fled
the jurisdiction.</font>

610
00:38:15,711 --> 00:38:17,379
<font color="#ffff80">His whereabouts are
currently unknown,</font>

611
00:38:17,588 --> 00:38:20,215
<font color="#ffff80">but he's being sought and pursued
by the relevant authorities.</font>

612
00:38:20,424 --> 00:38:22,509
<font color="#ffff80">Who is he?</font>

613
00:38:26,639 --> 00:38:27,640
<font color="#ffff80">Serge?</font>

614
00:38:27,765 --> 00:38:28,766
<font color="#ffff80">I'm afraid so.</font>

615
00:38:28,974 --> 00:38:31,226
<font color="#ffff80">That little prick.</font>

616
00:38:31,435 --> 00:38:33,562
<font color="#ffff80">No, I don't believe it.
They put him up to it.</font>

617
00:38:33,771 --> 00:38:35,898
<font color="#ffff80">I've been dropped into
a nest of vipers.</font>

618
00:38:36,106 --> 00:38:37,107
<font color="#ffff80">You have an alibi?</font>

619
00:38:37,316 --> 00:38:39,485
<font color="#ffff80">Of course, but she's married
to the Duke of Westphalia.</font>

620
00:38:39,693 --> 00:38:42,321
<font color="#ffff80">I can't allow her name to get
mixed-up in all this monkey business.</font>

621
00:38:42,529 --> 00:38:44,365
<font color="#ffff80">Your life may be at stake.</font>

622
00:38:44,490 --> 00:38:46,325
<font color="#ffff80">I know, but the bitch legged it.</font>

623
00:38:46,533 --> 00:38:50,287
<font color="#ffff80">She's already on board the Queen
<i>Nasstasja</i> halfway to Dutch Tanganyika.</font>

624
00:38:52,790 --> 00:38:54,041
<font color="#ffff80">Don't give up.</font>

625
00:38:59,880 --> 00:39:01,423
<font color="#ffff80"><i>MR. MOUSTAFA: The details
of the conspiracy,</i></font>

626
00:39:02,758 --> 00:39:04,885
<font color="#ffff80"><i>now a matter of public record,</i></font>

627
00:39:05,094 --> 00:39:08,222
<font color="#ffff80">were, <i>at that time, impossible
for us to apprehend.</i></font>

628
00:39:25,572 --> 00:39:27,116
<font color="#ffff80">I'm looking for Serge X,</font>

629
00:39:27,324 --> 00:39:30,160
<font color="#ffff80">a young man in the
service of my employer,</font>

630
00:39:30,369 --> 00:39:33,872
<font color="#ffff80">the family Desgoffe und
Taxis of Schloss Lutz.</font>

631
00:39:35,499 --> 00:39:37,084
<font color="#ffff80">Yes, sir? You're his sister?</font>

632
00:39:37,876 --> 00:39:39,670
<font color="#ffff80">Yes, sir. Seen him lately?</font>

633
00:39:40,838 --> 00:39:42,965
<font color="#ffff80">No, sir. No, sir?</font>

634
00:39:44,049 --> 00:39:45,050
<font color="#ffff80">No, sir.</font>

635
00:39:48,470 --> 00:39:51,265
<font color="#ffff80">I need to find him right
away, for his own safety</font>

636
00:39:51,473 --> 00:39:53,016
<font color="#ffff80">and everybody else's.</font>

637
00:39:53,225 --> 00:39:55,894
<font color="#ffff80">If he shows up...</font>

638
00:39:56,103 --> 00:39:58,856
<font color="#ffff80">Yes, sir? Tell him Jopling says,</font>

639
00:39:59,064 --> 00:40:01,316
<font color="#ffff80">"Come home."</font>

640
00:40:03,485 --> 00:40:06,071
<font color="#ffff80"><i>MR. MOUSTAFA: But one
thing was certain,</i></font>

641
00:40:08,115 --> 00:40:11,702
<font color="#ffff80"><i>the Desgoffe und Taxis were
a very powerful family,</i></font>

642
00:40:15,831 --> 00:40:18,041
<font color="#ffff80"><i>and time was not on our side.</i></font>

643
00:40:26,049 --> 00:40:28,844
<font color="#ffff80">A letter from Monsieur Gustave.
Zero.</font>

644
00:40:29,762 --> 00:40:31,764
<font color="#ffff80">You want me to? Read it.</font>

645
00:40:37,603 --> 00:40:39,563
<font color="#ffff80">"My dear and trusted
colleagues..."</font>

646
00:40:39,772 --> 00:40:41,815
<font color="#ffff80">I miss you deeply as I
write from the confines</font>

647
00:40:42,024 --> 00:40:45,027
<font color="#ffff80">of my regrettable and
preposterous incarceration.</font>

648
00:40:45,235 --> 00:40:47,321
<font color="#ffff80">Until I walk amongst you
again as a free man,</font>

649
00:40:47,529 --> 00:40:49,907
<font color="#ffff80">the Grand Budapest
remains in your hands,</font>

650
00:40:50,115 --> 00:40:52,284
<font color="#ffff80">as does its impeccable
reputation.</font>

651
00:40:52,493 --> 00:40:54,495
<font color="#ffff80">Keep it spotless and glorify it.</font>

652
00:40:54,703 --> 00:40:57,039
<font color="#ffff80">Take extra special care of
every little-bitty bit of it</font>

653
00:40:57,247 --> 00:40:59,333
<font color="#ffff80">as if I were watching
over you like a hawk</font>

654
00:40:59,541 --> 00:41:03,003
<font color="#ffff80">with a horse whip in its
talons, because I am.</font>

655
00:41:03,212 --> 00:41:06,256
<font color="#ffff80">Should I discover a lapse of
any variety during my absence,</font>

656
00:41:06,465 --> 00:41:10,093
<font color="#ffff80">I promise, swift and merciless
justice will descend upon you.</font>

657
00:41:10,302 --> 00:41:14,264
<font color="#ffff80">A great and noble house has been
placed under your protection.</font>

658
00:41:14,473 --> 00:41:17,100
<font color="#ffff80">Tell Zero if you see
any funny business.</font>

659
00:41:17,309 --> 00:41:19,436
<font color="#ffff80">"Your devoted Monsieur Gustave."</font>

660
00:41:19,645 --> 00:41:21,897
<font color="#ffff80">Then there's a poem, but we
might want to start on the soup</font>

661
00:41:22,105 --> 00:41:23,482
<font color="#ffff80">since it's 46 stanzas.</font>

662
00:41:24,691 --> 00:41:28,445
<font color="#ffff80">"A moist, black ash dampens the
filth of a dung-dark rat's nest</font>

663
00:41:28,654 --> 00:41:30,739
<font color="#ffff80">"and mingles with the
thick scent of wood rot</font>

664
00:41:30,948 --> 00:41:32,741
<font color="#ffff80">"while the lark song
of a guttersnipe..."</font>

665
00:41:32,950 --> 00:41:35,202
<font color="#ffff80">JOPLING: I never
trusted that butler.</font>

666
00:41:35,410 --> 00:41:37,204
<font color="#ffff80">He's too honest.</font>

667
00:41:37,329 --> 00:41:39,081
<font color="#ffff80">DMITRI ON PHONE: Too honest, you <i>say?
</i> JOPLING: Mmm-hmm.</font>

668
00:41:39,289 --> 00:41:41,416
<font color="#ffff80"><i>Right, well, be that as it may,</i></font>

669
00:41:41,583 --> 00:41:43,585
<font color="#ffff80"><i>find him quick and
make it snappy.</i></font>

670
00:41:59,893 --> 00:42:02,479
<font color="#ffff80">May I offer any of you
inmates a plate of mush?</font>

671
00:42:04,982 --> 00:42:06,400
<font color="#ffff80">No? Anyone?</font>

672
00:42:06,608 --> 00:42:08,861
<font color="#ffff80">You with the very large
scar on your face?</font>

673
00:42:18,245 --> 00:42:21,123
<font color="#ffff80">Try it. It's actually quite warm
and nourishing this morning.</font>

674
00:42:21,331 --> 00:42:22,374
<font color="#ffff80">It needs a dash of salt.</font>

675
00:42:31,258 --> 00:42:32,801
<font color="#ffff80">Good day.</font>

676
00:42:37,639 --> 00:42:39,641
<font color="#ffff80">Mush, gents? Any takers?</font>

677
00:42:43,770 --> 00:42:45,314
<font color="#ffff80">Suit yourselves.</font>

678
00:42:50,861 --> 00:42:52,529
<font color="#ffff80">Rise and shine. Chop, chop.</font>

679
00:42:54,114 --> 00:42:55,324
<font color="#ffff80">Good morning, Pinky.</font>

680
00:43:01,121 --> 00:43:02,414
<font color="#ffff80">Mendl's again?</font>

681
00:43:02,497 --> 00:43:03,707
<font color="#ffff80">Precisely.</font>

682
00:43:03,916 --> 00:43:05,918
<font color="#ffff80">Who's got the throat slitter?</font>

683
00:43:11,506 --> 00:43:12,925
<font color="#ffff80">Out of this world.</font>

684
00:43:13,050 --> 00:43:14,426
<font color="#ffff80">GUSTAVE H: Mendl's is the best.</font>

685
00:43:14,635 --> 00:43:16,762
<font color="#ffff80">Well, back to work.
Monsieur Gustave?</font>

686
00:43:20,349 --> 00:43:21,767
<font color="#ffff80">Yes?</font>

687
00:43:25,562 --> 00:43:27,856
<font color="#ffff80">PINKY: Me and the
boys talked it over.</font>

688
00:43:28,065 --> 00:43:30,525
<font color="#ffff80">We think you're a
really straight fellow.</font>

689
00:43:30,734 --> 00:43:32,903
<font color="#ffff80">Well, I've never been
accused of that before,</font>

690
00:43:33,111 --> 00:43:35,072
<font color="#ffff80">but I appreciate the sentiment.</font>

691
00:43:35,280 --> 00:43:36,657
<font color="#ffff80">You're one of us now.</font>

692
00:43:37,950 --> 00:43:39,910
<font color="#ffff80">What a lovely thing to say.</font>

693
00:43:40,118 --> 00:43:41,995
<font color="#ffff80">Thank you, dear Pinky.
Thank you, Gunther.</font>

694
00:43:42,204 --> 00:43:43,622
<font color="#ffff80">Thank you, Wolf.</font>

695
00:43:43,830 --> 00:43:45,832
<font color="#ffff80">Anything else?</font>

696
00:43:47,668 --> 00:43:48,710
<font color="#ffff80">Tell him, Ludwig.</font>

697
00:43:50,671 --> 00:43:53,966
<font color="#ffff80">Checkpoint 19 ain't
no two-bit hoosegow.</font>

698
00:43:54,174 --> 00:43:57,427
<font color="#ffff80">You got broad-gauge iron bars
on every door, vent and window.</font>

699
00:43:57,636 --> 00:44:01,223
<font color="#ffff80">You got 72 guards on the floor
and 16 more in the towers.</font>

700
00:44:01,431 --> 00:44:05,727
<font color="#ffff80">You got a 325-foot drop into
a moat full of crocodiles.</font>

701
00:44:05,936 --> 00:44:07,896
<font color="#ffff80">But, like the best of them,
it's got a soft spot,</font>

702
00:44:08,105 --> 00:44:09,856
<font color="#ffff80">which in this case
happens to take the form</font>

703
00:44:10,065 --> 00:44:12,192
<font color="#ffff80">of a storm-drain sewer system</font>

704
00:44:12,401 --> 00:44:14,695
<font color="#ffff80">dating from the time of the
original rock fortification</font>

705
00:44:14,903 --> 00:44:16,947
<font color="#ffff80">way back in the Middle Ages.</font>

706
00:44:17,155 --> 00:44:20,242
<font color="#ffff80">Now, nobody's saying it's a stroll
down a tree-lined promenade</font>

707
00:44:20,450 --> 00:44:22,202
<font color="#ffff80">with a fine lady and
a white poodle,</font>

708
00:44:22,411 --> 00:44:26,039
<font color="#ffff80">but it's got what you'd
call "vulnerability,"</font>

709
00:44:26,248 --> 00:44:28,917
<font color="#ffff80">and that's our bread and butter.</font>

710
00:44:29,751 --> 00:44:31,920
<font color="#ffff80">Take a look.</font>

711
00:44:33,130 --> 00:44:34,464
<font color="#ffff80">Who drew this?</font>

712
00:44:34,673 --> 00:44:36,758
<font color="#ffff80">What do you mean, "Who
drew this?" I did.</font>

713
00:44:36,967 --> 00:44:39,052
<font color="#ffff80">Very good. You've got a
wonderful line, Ludwig.</font>

714
00:44:39,261 --> 00:44:40,929
<font color="#ffff80">This <i>shows</i> great
artistic promise.</font>

715
00:44:41,138 --> 00:44:44,516
<font color="#ffff80">Question, how do you intend to
penetrate this lowest rudiment?</font>

716
00:44:44,725 --> 00:44:47,269
<font color="#ffff80">It's 25 inches of reinforced
granite masonry, is it not?</font>

717
00:44:47,477 --> 00:44:49,187
<font color="#ffff80">Digging with the throat-slitter,</font>

718
00:44:49,396 --> 00:44:52,024
<font color="#ffff80">I expect this would take three to
six months of continual effort,</font>

719
00:44:52,232 --> 00:44:53,734
<font color="#ffff80">during which time
several of our members</font>

720
00:44:53,942 --> 00:44:55,360
<font color="#ffff80">will have been
violently executed.</font>

721
00:44:55,569 --> 00:44:57,904
<font color="#ffff80">You hit the nail on the head, Mr.
Gustave.</font>

722
00:44:58,113 --> 00:45:00,699
<font color="#ffff80">We got fake documents,
second-hand street clothes,</font>

723
00:45:00,907 --> 00:45:03,285
<font color="#ffff80">a rope ladder made of
sticks and bunk-linens,</font>

724
00:45:03,493 --> 00:45:05,370
<font color="#ffff80">but we need digging tools,</font>

725
00:45:05,579 --> 00:45:08,540
<font color="#ffff80">which are proving hard to
come by in this flop-house.</font>

726
00:45:22,929 --> 00:45:24,473
<font color="#ffff80"><i>YOUNG</i> WRITER: <i>At this
point in the story,</i></font>

727
00:45:24,681 --> 00:45:28,268
<font color="#ffff80"><i>the old man fell silent and
pushed away his saddle of lamb.</i></font>

728
00:45:28,477 --> 00:45:31,313
<font color="#ffff80"><i>His eyes went blank
as two stones.</i></font>

729
00:45:31,521 --> 00:45:33,523
<font color="#ffff80"><i>I could see he was in distress.</i></font>

730
00:45:33,732 --> 00:45:34,941
<font color="#ffff80">Are you ill, Mr. Moustafa?</font>

731
00:45:35,067 --> 00:45:36,276
<font color="#ffff80"><i>I finally asked.</i></font>

732
00:45:36,485 --> 00:45:37,569
<font color="#ffff80">Oh, dear me, no.</font>

733
00:45:37,694 --> 00:45:38,779
<font color="#ffff80"><i>He said.</i></font>

734
00:45:38,987 --> 00:45:41,406
<font color="#ffff80">It's only that I don't
know how to proceed.</font>

735
00:45:42,616 --> 00:45:44,785
<font color="#ffff80"><i>He was crying.</i></font>

736
00:45:44,993 --> 00:45:46,495
<font color="#ffff80">You see, I never
speak of Agatha,</font>

737
00:45:46,703 --> 00:45:50,290
<font color="#ffff80">because even at the
thought of her name</font>

738
00:45:50,499 --> 00:45:53,251
<font color="#ffff80">I'm unable to control
my emotions.</font>

739
00:45:56,338 --> 00:45:58,590
<font color="#ffff80">Well, I suppose there's
no way around it.</font>

740
00:45:59,883 --> 00:46:02,219
<font color="#ffff80">You see, she saved us.</font>

741
00:46:02,511 --> 00:46:04,346
<font color="#ffff80"><i>On our third formal rendezvous,</i></font>

742
00:46:04,554 --> 00:46:07,474
<font color="#ffff80"><i>I had asked for her hand in
marriage and she had agreed.</i></font>

743
00:46:07,557 --> 00:46:09,559
<font color="#ffff80">Will you marry me? Yes.</font>

744
00:46:11,353 --> 00:46:14,231
<font color="#ffff80"><i>We did not have 50 Klubecks
between the two of us.</i></font>

745
00:46:14,439 --> 00:46:17,692
<font color="#ffff80"><i>No one knew, of course, but,
then, who would have cared?</i></font>

746
00:46:17,901 --> 00:46:20,654
<font color="#ffff80"><i>We were each completely
on our own in the world,</i></font>

747
00:46:21,780 --> 00:46:23,782
<font color="#ffff80"><i>and we were deeply in love.</i></font>

748
00:46:32,582 --> 00:46:34,417
<font color="#ffff80">Here. Thank you.</font>

749
00:46:34,626 --> 00:46:36,461
<font color="#ffff80">It's a book. I see.</font>

750
00:46:36,670 --> 00:46:38,171
<font color="#ffff80"><i>Romantic Poetry, Volume One.</i></font>

751
00:46:38,380 --> 00:46:39,506
<font color="#ffff80">Monsieur Gustave recommended it.</font>

752
00:46:39,631 --> 00:46:40,715
<font color="#ffff80">I have a copy of my own as well.</font>

753
00:46:40,924 --> 00:46:42,884
<font color="#ffff80">I ruined the
surprise, I suppose.</font>

754
00:46:43,009 --> 00:46:44,970
<font color="#ffff80">I'll go ahead and
open it, anyway.</font>

755
00:46:48,431 --> 00:46:50,433
<font color="#ffff80">Read the inscription.</font>

756
00:47:08,952 --> 00:47:10,036
<font color="#ffff80"><i>MR. MOUSTAFA: Monsieur
Gustave insisted</i></font>

757
00:47:10,245 --> 00:47:12,497
<font color="#ffff80"><i>on an immediate and thorough
cross-examination...</i></font>

758
00:47:12,706 --> 00:47:14,374
<font color="#ffff80">She's charming.
She's so charming.</font>

759
00:47:15,584 --> 00:47:18,003
<font color="#ffff80"><i>...during which he presented
Agatha with a porcelain pendant</i></font>

760
00:47:18,211 --> 00:47:21,131
<font color="#ffff80"><i>and five dozen individually
tissue-wrapped white tulips</i></font>

761
00:47:21,339 --> 00:47:23,466
<font color="#ffff80"><i>in a box the size of
a child's coffin.</i></font>

762
00:47:23,675 --> 00:47:24,968
<font color="#ffff80">It's not right.</font>

763
00:47:25,093 --> 00:47:26,386
<font color="#ffff80">I beg your pardon?</font>

764
00:47:26,595 --> 00:47:27,762
<font color="#ffff80">Why is he sulking?</font>

765
00:47:27,971 --> 00:47:29,848
<font color="#ffff80">She's my girlfriend. You
can't just buy her things.</font>

766
00:47:30,056 --> 00:47:33,393
<font color="#ffff80">I'm only interviewing this vision
of loveliness on your behalf.</font>

767
00:47:33,602 --> 00:47:36,188
<font color="#ffff80">Never be jealous in this life,
Zero, not even for an instant.</font>

768
00:47:36,396 --> 00:47:37,939
<font color="#ffff80">Is he flirting with you?</font>

769
00:47:39,232 --> 00:47:40,734
<font color="#ffff80">Yes.</font>

770
00:47:40,859 --> 00:47:42,360
<font color="#ffff80">I approve of this union.</font>

771
00:47:42,569 --> 00:47:45,071
<font color="#ffff80">Agatha, my beauty,
return to your beloved.</font>

772
00:47:45,280 --> 00:47:46,573
<font color="#ffff80">MR. MOUSTAFA: Soon we learned...</font>

773
00:47:46,781 --> 00:47:48,491
<font color="#ffff80">GUSTAVE H: Blessings
upon you both.</font>

774
00:47:48,700 --> 00:47:50,410
<font color="#ffff80"><i>...not only was Agatha
immensely skilled</i></font>

775
00:47:50,619 --> 00:47:53,121
<font color="#ffff80"><i>with a palette knife and a
butter-cream flourish...</i></font>

776
00:47:53,330 --> 00:47:55,332
<font color="#ffff80">Mendl. Go.</font>

777
00:47:56,499 --> 00:47:58,501
<font color="#ffff80"><i>...she was also very brave.</i></font>

778
00:48:02,964 --> 00:48:05,050
<font color="#ffff80"><i>I believe she was born that way.</i></font>

779
00:48:24,444 --> 00:48:26,488
<font color="#ffff80">Something's missing.</font>

780
00:48:26,696 --> 00:48:31,159
<font color="#ffff80">A crucial document, either misplaced
or, conceivably, destroyed.</font>

781
00:48:31,368 --> 00:48:33,870
<font color="#ffff80">I don't know what it contains, I
don't know what it represents,</font>

782
00:48:34,079 --> 00:48:35,455
<font color="#ffff80">I don't know what it is,</font>

783
00:48:35,664 --> 00:48:38,750
<font color="#ffff80">but there are traces and
shadows of it everywhere.</font>

784
00:48:38,959 --> 00:48:40,669
<font color="#ffff80">Now, I don't want to alarm you,</font>

785
00:48:40,877 --> 00:48:42,587
<font color="#ffff80">and I don't expect to see
any significant change</font>

786
00:48:42,796 --> 00:48:44,214
<font color="#ffff80">in the magistrate's
ultimate decision</font>

787
00:48:44,339 --> 00:48:45,799
<font color="#ffff80">vis-à-vis your own inheritance,</font>

788
00:48:46,007 --> 00:48:49,803
<font color="#ffff80">but, especially given the
circumstances of the death,</font>

789
00:48:50,011 --> 00:48:52,180
<font color="#ffff80">as well as the disappearance
of the key witness</font>

790
00:48:52,347 --> 00:48:54,474
<font color="#ffff80">in the murder case, Serge X,</font>

791
00:48:54,683 --> 00:48:56,351
<font color="#ffff80">I suggest that we immediately
bring this matter</font>

792
00:48:56,559 --> 00:48:58,770
<font color="#ffff80">to the attention of the
municipal inspector</font>

793
00:48:58,979 --> 00:49:00,730
<font color="#ffff80">so that there can be
absolutely no question</font>

794
00:49:00,939 --> 00:49:03,316
<font color="#ffff80">of impropriety at
any future date.</font>

795
00:49:03,525 --> 00:49:05,277
<font color="#ffff80">Agreed? Not agreed.</font>

796
00:49:07,112 --> 00:49:09,197
<font color="#ffff80">Not agreed? Not agreed.</font>

797
00:49:11,908 --> 00:49:13,493
<font color="#ffff80">Can I ask you a
question, Vilmos?</font>

798
00:49:13,618 --> 00:49:15,161
<font color="#ffff80">Yes, Dmitri?</font>

799
00:49:15,370 --> 00:49:16,663
<font color="#ffff80">Who are you working for?</font>

800
00:49:16,788 --> 00:49:18,039
<font color="#ffff80">I beg your pardon?</font>

801
00:49:18,248 --> 00:49:20,041
<font color="#ffff80">Who are you working for?</font>

802
00:49:20,208 --> 00:49:22,002
<font color="#ffff80">I thought you're supposed
to be our lawyer.</font>

803
00:49:22,210 --> 00:49:23,670
<font color="#ffff80">Well, in point of fact,</font>

804
00:49:23,753 --> 00:49:25,588
<font color="#ffff80">I'm the executor of the estate.</font>

805
00:49:25,797 --> 00:49:29,926
<font color="#ffff80">In this particular situation,
I represent the deceased.</font>

806
00:49:30,135 --> 00:49:31,136
<font color="#ffff80">Oh, yeah?</font>

807
00:49:31,261 --> 00:49:34,014
<font color="#ffff80">Yeah. A provision for my
fees was included in the...</font>

808
00:49:34,222 --> 00:49:39,019
<font color="#ffff80">Just wrap it up and don't make waves.
Agreed?</font>

809
00:49:41,021 --> 00:49:42,981
<font color="#ffff80">I'm an attorney.
I'm obligated to</font>

810
00:49:43,106 --> 00:49:45,066
<font color="#ffff80">proceed according
to the rule of law.</font>

811
00:49:46,443 --> 00:49:47,569
<font color="#ffff80">Not agreed.</font>

812
00:49:54,159 --> 00:49:56,202
<font color="#ffff80">This stinks, sisters.</font>

813
00:49:59,664 --> 00:50:01,708
<font color="#ffff80">Did he just throw my
cat out the window?</font>

814
00:50:03,001 --> 00:50:04,794
<font color="#ffff80">I don't think so.</font>

815
00:50:04,878 --> 00:50:05,879
<font color="#ffff80">No. Did he? Jopling?</font>

816
00:50:18,266 --> 00:50:19,768
<font color="#ffff80">Shh-shh.</font>

817
00:50:32,864 --> 00:50:34,866
<font color="#ffff80">LUDWIG: Okay.</font>

818
00:50:45,418 --> 00:50:48,171
<font color="#ffff80">There's something I
haven't told you, Agatha.</font>

819
00:50:48,380 --> 00:50:49,589
<font color="#ffff80">Okay. We stole a painting.</font>

820
00:50:49,798 --> 00:50:52,342
<font color="#ffff80">It's very valuable, maybe five
million Klubecks, in fact.</font>

821
00:50:52,550 --> 00:50:54,427
<font color="#ffff80">I don't know if anyone's even
noticed it's missing yet,</font>

822
00:50:54,636 --> 00:50:56,221
<font color="#ffff80">but if something
should happen to me...</font>

823
00:50:56,429 --> 00:50:57,931
<font color="#ffff80">You steal art?</font>

824
00:50:59,015 --> 00:51:02,060
<font color="#ffff80">One picture. Anyway, we need to
make a plan for your survival.</font>

825
00:51:02,268 --> 00:51:05,063
<font color="#ffff80">Hide this. It's in code and you might
need a magnifying glass to read it,</font>

826
00:51:05,271 --> 00:51:07,524
<font color="#ffff80">but it tells you exactly where
and how to find Boy <i>with</i> Apple.</font>

827
00:51:07,732 --> 00:51:09,776
<font color="#ffff80">Don't take less than half the
retail asking price. Also...</font>

828
00:51:09,984 --> 00:51:11,277
<font color="#ffff80">Zero, I'm a baker.</font>

829
00:51:11,403 --> 00:51:12,695
<font color="#ffff80">You're a pastry chef.</font>

830
00:51:12,904 --> 00:51:14,781
<font color="#ffff80">I'm not a fence, if
that's the term.</font>

831
00:51:14,989 --> 00:51:16,866
<font color="#ffff80">I don't trade in
stolen property.</font>

832
00:51:18,118 --> 00:51:19,953
<font color="#ffff80">I said it wrong. She
willed it to him.</font>

833
00:51:29,337 --> 00:51:31,339
<font color="#ffff80">Go to sleep.</font>

834
00:51:32,006 --> 00:51:33,842
<font color="#ffff80"><i>Yes, Herr Mendl.</i></font>

835
00:51:36,594 --> 00:51:38,346
<font color="#ffff80">Hide this. No.</font>

836
00:51:38,555 --> 00:51:40,557
<font color="#ffff80">Okay, but take it anyway.</font>

837
00:55:06,554 --> 00:55:09,766
<font color="#ffff80"><i>MR. MOUSTAFA: The next morning,
Herr Becker received</i> a <i>peculiar,</i></font>

838
00:55:09,974 --> 00:55:12,685
<font color="#ffff80"><i>last-minute notice from the
office of Deputy Kovacs,</i></font>

839
00:55:12,894 --> 00:55:17,357
<font color="#ffff80"><i>postponing their scheduled
meeting, in perpetuity.</i></font>

840
00:55:47,470 --> 00:55:49,472
<font color="#ffff80">LUDWIG: Let's blow.</font>

841
00:56:59,250 --> 00:57:00,501
<font color="#ffff80">How did you get out there?</font>

842
00:57:00,626 --> 00:57:01,878
<font color="#ffff80">Shut the fuck up.</font>

843
00:57:02,086 --> 00:57:04,714
<font color="#ffff80">These guys are trying to escape.</font>

844
00:57:04,922 --> 00:57:06,632
<font color="#ffff80">What's wrong with you,
you goddamn snitch?</font>

845
00:57:06,841 --> 00:57:08,843
<font color="#ffff80">Guard! Guard!</font>

846
00:57:16,142 --> 00:57:17,393
<font color="#ffff80">It's you. Thank you.</font>

847
00:57:17,477 --> 00:57:19,604
<font color="#ffff80">Thank you, you sweet, kind man.</font>

848
00:57:49,467 --> 00:57:51,469
<font color="#ffff80">LUDWIG: Okay.</font>

849
00:58:43,521 --> 00:58:44,855
<font color="#ffff80">ALL: Whoa!</font>

850
00:59:05,501 --> 00:59:08,129
<font color="#ffff80">I suppose you'd
call that a draw.</font>

851
00:59:17,263 --> 00:59:19,265
<font color="#ffff80">Good evening.</font>

852
00:59:27,523 --> 00:59:31,152
<font color="#ffff80">Let me introduce you. Pinky, Wolf,
Ludwig, this is the divine Zero.</font>

853
00:59:31,360 --> 00:59:33,195
<font color="#ffff80">Gunther was slain
in the catacombs.</font>

854
00:59:33,446 --> 00:59:36,198
<font color="#ffff80">Well, boys, who knows when we'll
all meet again, but if one clay...</font>

855
00:59:36,449 --> 00:59:37,491
<font color="#ffff80">Hold it.</font>

856
00:59:40,494 --> 00:59:42,872
<font color="#ffff80">No time to gab.</font>

857
00:59:43,122 --> 00:59:45,499
<font color="#ffff80">Take care of yourself, Mr.
Gustave.</font>

858
00:59:45,666 --> 00:59:47,668
<font color="#ffff80">Good luck, kid.</font>

859
00:59:51,297 --> 00:59:52,798
<font color="#ffff80">Which way to the safe house?</font>

860
00:59:52,923 --> 00:59:54,383
<font color="#ffff80">I couldn't find one.</font>

861
00:59:54,508 --> 00:59:57,553
<font color="#ffff80">No safe house? Really? We're
completely on our own out here?</font>

862
00:59:57,720 --> 01:00:00,890
<font color="#ffff80">I'm afraid so. I
asked around, but...</font>

863
01:00:01,140 --> 01:00:03,893
<font color="#ffff80">GUSTAVE H: I understand. Too risky.
We'll just have to wing it, I suppose.</font>

864
01:00:04,143 --> 01:00:06,520
<font color="#ffff80">Let's put on our disguises.</font>

865
01:00:06,687 --> 01:00:07,730
<font color="#ffff80">We're wearing them.</font>

866
01:00:07,855 --> 01:00:08,856
<font color="#ffff80">No, we're not.</font>

867
01:00:09,065 --> 01:00:11,525
<font color="#ffff80">We said false whiskers and
fake noses and so on.</font>

868
01:00:11,692 --> 01:00:12,860
<font color="#ffff80">You didn't bring any?</font>

869
01:00:13,027 --> 01:00:14,195
<font color="#ffff80">I thought you were growing one.</font>

870
01:00:14,403 --> 01:00:17,323
<font color="#ffff80">And it wouldn't look
realistic, would it?</font>

871
01:00:17,531 --> 01:00:19,700
<font color="#ffff80">No, when done properly,
they're perfectly convincing.</font>

872
01:00:19,909 --> 01:00:21,869
<font color="#ffff80">But I take your point. So be it.</font>

873
01:00:22,036 --> 01:00:24,497
<font color="#ffff80">Give me a few squirts of L'air
de Panache, please, will you?</font>

874
01:00:26,207 --> 01:00:27,833
<font color="#ffff80">Can I not get a squirt, even?</font>

875
01:00:27,958 --> 01:00:29,543
<font color="#ffff80">I forgot the L'air de Panache.</font>

876
01:00:29,752 --> 01:00:32,338
<font color="#ffff80">Honestly, you forgot
the L'air de Panache?</font>

877
01:00:32,546 --> 01:00:35,508
<font color="#ffff80">I don't believe it.
How could you?</font>

878
01:00:35,716 --> 01:00:38,678
<font color="#ffff80">I've been in jail, Zero! Do you
understand how humiliating this is?</font>

879
01:00:38,886 --> 01:00:40,888
<font color="#ffff80">I smell.</font>

880
01:00:42,390 --> 01:00:44,767
<font color="#ffff80">That's just marvelous, isn't it?</font>

881
01:00:45,017 --> 01:00:47,228
<font color="#ffff80">I suppose this is to
be expected back in...</font>

882
01:00:47,311 --> 01:00:48,729
<font color="#ffff80">Where do you come from again?</font>

883
01:00:48,938 --> 01:00:50,439
<font color="#ffff80">Aq Salim al-Jabat. Precisely.</font>

884
01:00:50,690 --> 01:00:53,234
<font color="#ffff80">I suppose this is to be expected
back in Aq Salim al-Jabat</font>

885
01:00:53,401 --> 01:00:54,694
<font color="#ffff80">where one's prized possessions</font>

886
01:00:54,902 --> 01:00:56,737
<font color="#ffff80">are a stack of filthy carpets
and a starving goat,</font>

887
01:00:56,946 --> 01:01:00,741
<font color="#ffff80">and one sleeps behind a tent flap and
survives on wild dates and scarabs.</font>

888
01:01:00,950 --> 01:01:03,452
<font color="#ffff80">But it's not how I trained you.</font>

889
01:01:03,703 --> 01:01:05,329
<font color="#ffff80">What on God's earth
possessed you to leave</font>

890
01:01:05,413 --> 01:01:06,747
<font color="#ffff80">the homeland where
you obviously belong</font>

891
01:01:06,914 --> 01:01:08,290
<font color="#ffff80">and travel unspeakable distances</font>

892
01:01:08,416 --> 01:01:11,961
<font color="#ffff80">to become a penniless immigrant in a
refined, highly-cultivated society</font>

893
01:01:12,211 --> 01:01:15,214
<font color="#ffff80">that, quite frankly, could've
gotten along very well without you?</font>

894
01:01:16,132 --> 01:01:17,133
<font color="#ffff80">The war.</font>

895
01:01:18,259 --> 01:01:19,593
<font color="#ffff80">Say again?</font>

896
01:01:19,760 --> 01:01:21,804
<font color="#ffff80">Well, you see, my
father was murdered</font>

897
01:01:22,054 --> 01:01:24,640
<font color="#ffff80">and the rest of my family were
executed by firing squad.</font>

898
01:01:24,890 --> 01:01:26,308
<font color="#ffff80">Our village was
burned to the ground</font>

899
01:01:26,559 --> 01:01:29,770
<font color="#ffff80">and those who managed to
survive were forced to flee.</font>

900
01:01:29,937 --> 01:01:31,772
<font color="#ffff80">I left because of the war.</font>

901
01:01:32,732 --> 01:01:36,444
<font color="#ffff80">I see. So you're, actually, really
more of a refugee, in that sense?</font>

902
01:01:37,611 --> 01:01:38,612
<font color="#ffff80">Truly.</font>

903
01:01:38,779 --> 01:01:42,491
<font color="#ffff80">Well, I suppose I'd better take
back everything I just said.</font>

904
01:01:43,743 --> 01:01:46,829
<font color="#ffff80">What a bloody idiot I am.
Pathetic fool.</font>

905
01:01:47,079 --> 01:01:49,165
<font color="#ffff80">Goddamn, selfish bastard.</font>

906
01:01:49,415 --> 01:01:52,460
<font color="#ffff80">This is disgraceful, and it's beneath
the standards of the Grand Budapest.</font>

907
01:01:54,128 --> 01:01:56,172
<font color="#ffff80">I apologize on
behalf of the hotel.</font>

908
01:01:56,422 --> 01:01:58,758
<font color="#ffff80">It's not your fault. You were
just upset I forgot the perfume.</font>

909
01:01:58,966 --> 01:02:02,970
<font color="#ffff80">Don't make excuses for me.
I owe you my life.</font>

910
01:02:03,179 --> 01:02:07,016
<font color="#ffff80">You are my dear friend and protégé
and I'm very proud of you.</font>

911
01:02:07,266 --> 01:02:09,518
<font color="#ffff80">You must know that.</font>

912
01:02:09,769 --> 01:02:11,771
<font color="#ffff80">I'm so sorry, Zero.</font>

913
01:02:13,314 --> 01:02:15,316
<font color="#ffff80">We're brothers.</font>

914
01:02:23,491 --> 01:02:25,493
<font color="#ffff80">How's our darling Agatha?</font>

915
01:02:27,953 --> 01:02:31,207
<font color="#ffff80">"'Twas first light when I saw
her face upon the heath,</font>

916
01:02:31,457 --> 01:02:34,043
<font color="#ffff80">"and hence did I return,
day-by-day, entranced,</font>

917
01:02:34,293 --> 01:02:37,171
<font color="#ffff80">"tho' vinegar did brine
my heart, never..."</font>

918
01:02:37,338 --> 01:02:40,007
<font color="#ffff80">Very good. I'm going to stop you
there because the alarm has sounded,</font>

919
01:02:40,216 --> 01:02:43,677
<font color="#ffff80">but remember where we left off
because I insist you finish later.</font>

920
01:03:01,695 --> 01:03:04,448
<font color="#ffff80">I want roadblocks at
every junction for 50km.</font>

921
01:03:04,657 --> 01:03:07,368
<font color="#ffff80">I want rail blocks at every
train station for 100km.</font>

922
01:03:07,618 --> 01:03:09,203
<font color="#ffff80">I want 50 men and 10 bloodhounds</font>

923
01:03:09,286 --> 01:03:10,454
<font color="#ffff80">ready in five minutes.</font>

924
01:03:10,663 --> 01:03:12,206
<font color="#ffff80">We're going to strip-search</font>

925
01:03:12,331 --> 01:03:13,874
<font color="#ffff80">every pretzel-Ha us,
Waffel-hut, Biergarten</font>

926
01:03:14,041 --> 01:03:16,126
<font color="#ffff80">and especially every grand hotel</font>

927
01:03:16,210 --> 01:03:17,837
<font color="#ffff80">from Äugenzburg to Zilchbrück.</font>

928
01:03:18,128 --> 01:03:20,047
<font color="#ffff80">These men are dangerous,
professional criminals.</font>

929
01:03:20,297 --> 01:03:22,341
<font color="#ffff80">At least three of
them are anyway.</font>

930
01:03:22,550 --> 01:03:23,551
<font color="#ffff80">Who are you?</font>

931
01:03:25,970 --> 01:03:26,971
<font color="#ffff80">What are you doing here?</font>

932
01:03:27,054 --> 01:03:28,722
<font color="#ffff80">Civilian personnel aren't
permitted in the cellblock.</font>

933
01:03:28,806 --> 01:03:30,307
<font color="#ffff80">This is a military
investigation.</font>

934
01:03:30,432 --> 01:03:31,934
<font color="#ffff80">This is Mr. Jopling, sir.</font>

935
01:03:32,017 --> 01:03:34,228
<font color="#ffff80">His employer's mother was
one of the victims...</font>

936
01:03:34,395 --> 01:03:36,730
<font color="#ffff80">Shut up.</font>

937
01:03:37,731 --> 01:03:40,067
<font color="#ffff80">You work for the family
Desgoffe und Taxis?</font>

938
01:03:40,234 --> 01:03:44,196
<font color="#ffff80">Are you aware of the murder of Deputy
Vilmos Kovacs on 23rd October?</font>

939
01:03:44,405 --> 01:03:46,740
<font color="#ffff80">I'm aware of his disappearance.</font>

940
01:03:46,991 --> 01:03:49,493
<font color="#ffff80">His body was found stuffed in a
sarcophagus behind a storage room</font>

941
01:03:49,702 --> 01:03:51,245
<font color="#ffff80">at the Kunstmuseum
late last night.</font>

942
01:03:51,495 --> 01:03:54,081
<font color="#ffff80"><i>He was short four fingers.</i></font>

943
01:03:54,248 --> 01:03:55,541
<font color="#ffff80">What do you know about that?</font>

944
01:03:55,666 --> 01:03:56,917
<font color="#ffff80">Nothing.</font>

945
01:03:58,586 --> 01:04:00,588
<font color="#ffff80">Escort Mr. Jopling
off the premises.</font>

946
01:04:11,098 --> 01:04:13,100
<font color="#ffff80">Mendl's.</font>

947
01:04:17,897 --> 01:04:20,107
<font color="#ffff80">Operator, get me the Excelsior
Palace in Baden-Jurgen</font>

948
01:04:20,274 --> 01:04:21,775
<font color="#ffff80">and reverse the charges, please.</font>

949
01:04:22,026 --> 01:04:23,861
<font color="#ffff80">We've no choice. There's
nowhere else to turn.</font>

950
01:04:24,069 --> 01:04:25,362
<font color="#ffff80">I'll hold. Thank you.</font>

951
01:04:25,571 --> 01:04:28,282
<font color="#ffff80">It's our only hope. Otherwise, I shouldn't
even mention its existence to you.</font>

952
01:04:28,449 --> 01:04:31,243
<font color="#ffff80">It goes without saying, never breathe
a word about this to a living soul.</font>

953
01:04:31,452 --> 01:04:33,203
<font color="#ffff80">Do you swear? Of course.
What is it, in fact?</font>

954
01:04:33,412 --> 01:04:34,538
<font color="#ffff80">I can't say.</font>

955
01:04:37,207 --> 01:04:38,959
<font color="#ffff80">How does one come by
front-row aisle seats</font>

956
01:04:39,209 --> 01:04:42,463
<font color="#ffff80">for a first night at the Opera
Toscana with one day's notice?</font>

957
01:04:42,630 --> 01:04:44,131
<font color="#ffff80">How does one arrange
a private viewing</font>

958
01:04:44,381 --> 01:04:47,134
<font color="#ffff80">of the tapestry collection
at the Royal Saxon Gallery?</font>

959
01:04:47,301 --> 01:04:51,472
<font color="#ffff80">How does one secure a corner table
at Chez Dominique on a Thursday?</font>

960
01:04:51,639 --> 01:04:53,933
<font color="#ffff80">Ivan, darling, it's Gustave.
Hello.</font>

961
01:04:54,141 --> 01:04:56,143
<font color="#ffff80">Well, I was until about
five minutes ago.</font>

962
01:04:56,393 --> 01:04:59,480
<font color="#ffff80">We've taken it upon ourselves to clear
out in a hurry if you see what I mean.</font>

963
01:04:59,647 --> 01:05:02,149
<font color="#ffff80">Well, through a sewer, as it happens.
Exactly.</font>

964
01:05:02,316 --> 01:05:04,985
<font color="#ffff80">Listen, Ivan, I'm sorry to out you
off, but we're in a bit of a bind.</font>

965
01:05:05,152 --> 01:05:06,820
<font color="#ffff80">This is an official request.</font>

966
01:05:06,987 --> 01:05:10,157
<font color="#ffff80">I'm formally calling upon
the special services of...</font>

967
01:05:15,412 --> 01:05:16,830
<font color="#ffff80">IVAN: <i>I'll call you
back, Gustave.</i></font>

968
01:05:17,081 --> 01:05:18,999
<font color="#ffff80">Right. Stand by.</font>

969
01:05:19,249 --> 01:05:22,419
<font color="#ffff80">I beg your pardon. Do
you prefer to walk?</font>

970
01:05:22,628 --> 01:05:24,505
<font color="#ffff80">We're right here.
It's very simple.</font>

971
01:05:24,755 --> 01:05:26,757
<font color="#ffff80">Straight down the
corniche, then left.</font>

972
01:05:26,966 --> 01:05:28,968
<font color="#ffff80">Jojo, see the gentleman out.</font>

973
01:05:31,845 --> 01:05:34,139
<font color="#ffff80">Get me Monsieur Georges at
the Château Luxe, please.</font>

974
01:05:35,933 --> 01:05:38,310
<font color="#ffff80"><i>Happy birthday to you</i></font>

975
01:05:39,603 --> 01:05:40,604
<font color="#ffff80">Take over.</font>

976
01:05:40,688 --> 01:05:42,106
<font color="#ffff80"><i>Happy birthday, dear...</i></font>

977
01:05:42,272 --> 01:05:43,524
<font color="#ffff80">GEORGES: Hello, Ivan?</font>

978
01:05:45,693 --> 01:05:47,528
<font color="#ffff80">Got it.</font>

979
01:05:47,778 --> 01:05:50,531
<font color="#ffff80">Get me Monsieur Dino at the
Palazzo Principessa, please.</font>

980
01:05:52,282 --> 01:05:54,618
<font color="#ffff80">Higher, goddammit, higher!</font>

981
01:05:56,537 --> 01:05:58,205
<font color="#ffff80">Take over.</font>

982
01:05:58,372 --> 01:05:59,957
<font color="#ffff80">DINO: Monsieur Georges. Higher.</font>

983
01:06:00,165 --> 01:06:02,334
<font color="#ffff80">I see. Straightaway.</font>

984
01:06:03,877 --> 01:06:06,380
<font color="#ffff80">Get me Monsieur Robin at
I'Hôtel Côte du Cap, please.</font>

985
01:06:08,132 --> 01:06:10,009
<font color="#ffff80">...and two and three.</font>

986
01:06:11,301 --> 01:06:14,138
<font color="#ffff80">Monsieur Robin. There's a call
from Monsieur Dino for you.</font>

987
01:06:14,346 --> 01:06:16,348
<font color="#ffff80">Take over.</font>

988
01:06:17,725 --> 01:06:19,059
<font color="#ffff80">One, two, three.</font>

989
01:06:19,184 --> 01:06:20,477
<font color="#ffff80"><i>ROBIN: Yes, Dino.</i></font>

990
01:06:20,686 --> 01:06:23,981
<font color="#ffff80">Yes, Dino. Okay, Dino.</font>

991
01:06:25,733 --> 01:06:28,318
<font color="#ffff80">Get me Monsieur Martin at
the Ritz Imperial, please.</font>

992
01:06:30,029 --> 01:06:31,905
<font color="#ffff80">Too much salt.</font>

993
01:06:32,072 --> 01:06:33,615
<font color="#ffff80">Not enough pepper-</font>

994
01:06:35,200 --> 01:06:37,202
<font color="#ffff80">Take over.</font>

995
01:06:39,246 --> 01:06:41,331
<font color="#ffff80"><i>Robin? Martin. Too much salt.</i></font>

996
01:06:41,540 --> 01:06:43,542
<font color="#ffff80">So I've heard.</font>

997
01:06:44,877 --> 01:06:47,838
<font color="#ffff80">Maybe. Let me make a few calls.</font>

998
01:06:52,926 --> 01:06:55,429
<font color="#ffff80">Serge X, missing. Deputy
Kovacs, also missing.</font>

999
01:06:55,596 --> 01:06:58,432
<font color="#ffff80">Madame D, dead. Boy <i>with
</i> Apple, stolen, by us.</font>

1000
01:06:58,599 --> 01:07:01,060
<font color="#ffff80">Dmitri and Jopling, ruthless,
cold-blooded savages.</font>

1001
01:07:01,268 --> 01:07:04,521
<font color="#ffff80">Gustave H, at large. What else?</font>

1002
01:07:04,730 --> 01:07:06,023
<font color="#ffff80">Zero, confused.</font>

1003
01:07:06,148 --> 01:07:07,441
<font color="#ffff80">Zero, confused, indeed.</font>

1004
01:07:07,608 --> 01:07:09,777
<font color="#ffff80">The plot "thickens,"
as they say.</font>

1005
01:07:10,027 --> 01:07:12,613
<font color="#ffff80">Why, by the way? Is
it a soup metaphor?</font>

1006
01:07:12,863 --> 01:07:14,865
<font color="#ffff80">I don't know.</font>

1007
01:07:19,703 --> 01:07:21,288
<font color="#ffff80">Get in.</font>

1008
01:07:23,749 --> 01:07:25,042
<font color="#ffff80">IVAN: We found the butler.</font>

1009
01:07:25,250 --> 01:07:28,045
<font color="#ffff80">He's hiding out in the remote
foothills near Gabelmeister's Peak.</font>

1010
01:07:28,253 --> 01:07:30,380
<font color="#ffff80">Our contact convinced him
to meet you midday tomorrow</font>

1011
01:07:30,589 --> 01:07:31,965
<font color="#ffff80">at the observatory
on the summit.</font>

1012
01:07:32,132 --> 01:07:34,468
<font color="#ffff80">Tell no one. He'll
explain everything.</font>

1013
01:07:34,718 --> 01:07:36,762
<font color="#ffff80">Your train departs in
four and a half minutes.</font>

1014
01:07:36,970 --> 01:07:38,388
<font color="#ffff80">Here's your tickets.</font>

1015
01:07:38,597 --> 01:07:39,640
<font color="#ffff80">Third class?</font>

1016
01:07:39,807 --> 01:07:40,808
<font color="#ffff80">It was overbooked</font>

1017
01:07:41,058 --> 01:07:44,645
<font color="#ffff80">but the conductor used to be a
sommelier at the old Versailles.</font>

1018
01:07:44,812 --> 01:07:45,979
<font color="#ffff80">He pulled some strings.</font>

1019
01:07:46,271 --> 01:07:48,273
<font color="#ffff80">You'll need these
for the dining car.</font>

1020
01:07:51,151 --> 01:07:53,153
<font color="#ffff80">One last thing.</font>

1021
01:07:54,822 --> 01:07:56,824
<font color="#ffff80">L'air de Panache.</font>

1022
01:07:59,326 --> 01:08:01,495
<font color="#ffff80">They only had the half-ounce.</font>

1023
01:08:05,791 --> 01:08:07,793
<font color="#ffff80">We should give him something
as a symbolic gesture.</font>

1024
01:08:08,001 --> 01:08:10,254
<font color="#ffff80">How much money you got? 42
Klubecks and 3 postage stamps.</font>

1025
01:08:10,462 --> 01:08:12,464
<font color="#ffff80">Give me 25. Yes.</font>

1026
01:08:16,176 --> 01:08:17,553
<font color="#ffff80">Bless you.</font>

1027
01:08:17,678 --> 01:08:19,096
<font color="#ffff80">Please.</font>

1028
01:08:35,487 --> 01:08:36,572
<font color="#ffff80">JOPLING: I've got
to hand it to him.</font>

1029
01:08:36,655 --> 01:08:37,656
<font color="#ffff80">DMITRI ON PHONE: <i>Jesus</i> Christ.</font>

1030
01:08:37,823 --> 01:08:41,577
<font color="#ffff80">JOPLING: I didn't see that coming.
Well, what do you want next?</font>

1031
01:08:41,702 --> 01:08:47,040
<font color="#ffff80">DMITRI: <i>Talk to the club-footed sister
again, and, this time, be persuasive.</i></font>

1032
01:08:54,173 --> 01:08:56,967
<font color="#ffff80">DMITRI: Goddamn son of a bitch.</font>

1033
01:09:20,532 --> 01:09:22,534
<font color="#ffff80">Holy fuck!</font>

1034
01:09:26,872 --> 01:09:29,750
<font color="#ffff80">What's the meaning of this shit?</font>

1035
01:09:29,917 --> 01:09:31,543
<font color="#ffff80">Boy <i>with Apple?</i> I thought
you'd hidden it.</font>

1036
01:09:31,627 --> 01:09:34,087
<font color="#ffff80">Why are you only noticing now? I
assumed it went to the tax appraiser.</font>

1037
01:09:34,338 --> 01:09:36,006
<font color="#ffff80">Are you fucking kidding me?</font>

1038
01:09:36,089 --> 01:09:38,091
<font color="#ffff80"><i>CLOTILDE: Excusez-moi.</i></font>

1039
01:09:38,592 --> 01:09:41,386
<font color="#ffff80">I believe it was removed
by Monsieur Gustave.</font>

1040
01:09:49,269 --> 01:09:50,395
<font color="#ffff80">I'm not angry with Serge.</font>

1041
01:09:50,604 --> 01:09:53,065
<font color="#ffff80">You can't blame someone for their
basic lack of moral fiber.</font>

1042
01:09:53,273 --> 01:09:55,234
<font color="#ffff80">He's a frightened, little,
yellow-bellied coward.</font>

1043
01:09:55,442 --> 01:09:57,444
<font color="#ffff80">It's not his fault, is it? I don't know.
It depends.</font>

1044
01:09:57,694 --> 01:09:59,238
<font color="#ffff80">Well, you can say that
about most anything.</font>

1045
01:09:59,321 --> 01:10:00,739
<font color="#ffff80">"It depends." Of
course it depends.</font>

1046
01:10:00,948 --> 01:10:02,449
<font color="#ffff80">Of course it depends.
Of course it depends.</font>

1047
01:10:02,699 --> 01:10:04,785
<font color="#ffff80">Yes, I suppose you're right.
Of course it depends.</font>

1048
01:10:05,035 --> 01:10:08,455
<font color="#ffff80">That doesn't mean I'm not going
to throttle the little swamp rat.</font>

1049
01:10:10,958 --> 01:10:15,254
<font color="#ffff80">May I officiate, by the way?
The ceremony?</font>

1050
01:10:15,462 --> 01:10:16,463
<font color="#ffff80">With pleasure.</font>

1051
01:10:16,630 --> 01:10:19,258
<font color="#ffff80">I must say, I find that
girl utterly delightful.</font>

1052
01:10:19,466 --> 01:10:20,968
<font color="#ffff80">Flat as a board,
enormous birthmark</font>

1053
01:10:21,218 --> 01:10:22,970
<font color="#ffff80">the shape of Mexico
over half her face,</font>

1054
01:10:23,220 --> 01:10:25,305
<font color="#ffff80">sweating for hours on end
in that sweltering kitchen</font>

1055
01:10:25,472 --> 01:10:26,890
<font color="#ffff80">while Mendl, genius
though he is,</font>

1056
01:10:27,099 --> 01:10:28,642
<font color="#ffff80">looms over her like
a hulking gorilla.</font>

1057
01:10:28,892 --> 01:10:31,061
<font color="#ffff80">Yet without question,
without fail,</font>

1058
01:10:31,270 --> 01:10:34,481
<font color="#ffff80">always and invariably,
she's exceedingly lovely.</font>

1059
01:10:34,648 --> 01:10:35,983
<font color="#ffff80">Why?</font>

1060
01:10:36,233 --> 01:10:38,819
<font color="#ffff80">Because of her purity.</font>

1061
01:10:40,904 --> 01:10:43,156
<font color="#ffff80">She admires you as well,
Monsieur Gustave.</font>

1062
01:10:43,323 --> 01:10:44,658
<font color="#ffff80">Does she?</font>

1063
01:10:44,783 --> 01:10:46,076
<font color="#ffff80">Very much.</font>

1064
01:10:46,285 --> 01:10:50,080
<font color="#ffff80">That's a good sign, you know.
It means she "gets it."</font>

1065
01:10:50,289 --> 01:10:52,291
<font color="#ffff80">That's important.</font>

1066
01:10:54,751 --> 01:10:56,753
<font color="#ffff80">Don't flirt with her.</font>

1067
01:11:42,632 --> 01:11:46,053
<font color="#ffff80">LIEUTENANT: A radio telegram was delivered
and signed for by the girl at 4:00 AM.</font>

1068
01:11:46,219 --> 01:11:48,889
<font color="#ffff80">The envelope was found near the body,
but its contents were missing.</font>

1069
01:11:49,639 --> 01:11:50,974
<font color="#ffff80">However, the telegraph
office always keeps</font>

1070
01:11:51,058 --> 01:11:52,809
<font color="#ffff80">a carbon of the ticker
tape for 24 hours.</font>

1071
01:11:53,018 --> 01:11:55,228
<font color="#ffff80">I copied it down. It
reads as follows,</font>

1072
01:11:56,229 --> 01:11:57,397
<font color="#ffff80">"Pack your things stop.</font>

1073
01:11:57,647 --> 01:11:59,733
<font color="#ffff80">"Be ready to leave at
moment's notice stop.</font>

1074
01:11:59,900 --> 01:12:02,361
<font color="#ffff80">"Hide-out is vicinity of
Gabelmeister's Peak stop.</font>

1075
01:12:02,569 --> 01:12:04,988
<font color="#ffff80">"Destroy this message
all my love full stop."</font>

1076
01:12:06,073 --> 01:12:07,866
<font color="#ffff80">Where's the basket?</font>

1077
01:12:33,183 --> 01:12:35,185
<font color="#ffff80">PUMP ATTENDANT: Where
you headed, mister?</font>

1078
01:12:38,897 --> 01:12:41,233
<font color="#ffff80">Skiing? Sledding?
Mountain climbing?</font>

1079
01:12:50,951 --> 01:12:52,911
<font color="#ffff80">Three Klubecks.</font>

1080
01:13:03,046 --> 01:13:04,798
<font color="#ffff80"><i>MR. MOUSTAFA: By express
wireless, I wrote Agatha</i></font>

1081
01:13:05,048 --> 01:13:07,801
<font color="#ffff80"><i>with instructions to move to
our pre-arranged hideout,</i></font>

1082
01:13:07,968 --> 01:13:10,470
<font color="#ffff80"><i>a Gypsy caravan on the
outer Nebelsbad road,</i></font>

1083
01:13:10,720 --> 01:13:12,472
<font color="#ffff80"><i>while Monsieur Gustave
and I continued east</i></font>

1084
01:13:12,722 --> 01:13:14,099
<font color="#ffff80"><i>into the Zubrowkian Alps,</i></font>

1085
01:13:14,307 --> 01:13:18,061
<font color="#ffff80"><i>toward our high-altitude rendezvous
with the butler Serge X.</i></font>

1086
01:13:19,980 --> 01:13:22,274
<font color="#ffff80"><i>As a precaution, we
disembarked quietly</i></font>

1087
01:13:22,482 --> 01:13:24,901
<font color="#ffff80"><i>in the freight yard just
outside the station.</i></font>

1088
01:13:32,492 --> 01:13:34,327
<font color="#ffff80">L'air de Panache.</font>

1089
01:13:44,963 --> 01:13:47,257
<font color="#ffff80">It's a hell of a view. I give
them that, for what's it's worth.</font>

1090
01:13:47,465 --> 01:13:49,467
<font color="#ffff80">I agree.</font>

1091
01:14:00,520 --> 01:14:03,982
<font color="#ffff80">"'Tis oft'-remarked, no single,
falling-flake does any other</font>

1092
01:14:04,232 --> 01:14:07,819
<font color="#ffff80">"in its pure and perfect
form..." Somebody's coming.</font>

1093
01:14:10,363 --> 01:14:13,533
<font color="#ffff80">Are you Monsieur Gustave of the
Grand Budapest Hotel in Nebelsbad?</font>

1094
01:14:13,700 --> 01:14:14,993
<font color="#ffff80">Uh-huh.</font>

1095
01:14:15,118 --> 01:14:16,369
<font color="#ffff80">Get on the next cable car.</font>

1096
01:14:55,909 --> 01:14:59,329
<font color="#ffff80">Are you Monsieur Gustave of the
Grand Budapest Hotel in Nebelsbad?</font>

1097
01:14:59,537 --> 01:15:00,538
<font color="#ffff80">Uh-huh.</font>

1098
01:15:00,664 --> 01:15:01,665
<font color="#ffff80">Switch with me.</font>

1099
01:15:31,236 --> 01:15:33,947
<font color="#ffff80">Are you Monsieur Gustave of the
Grand Budapest Hotel in Nebelsbad?</font>

1100
01:15:34,197 --> 01:15:35,532
<font color="#ffff80">Uh-huh.</font>

1101
01:15:35,657 --> 01:15:36,950
<font color="#ffff80">Put these on and sing.</font>

1102
01:16:02,475 --> 01:16:03,935
<font color="#ffff80">MONK: Psst.</font>

1103
01:16:05,103 --> 01:16:06,271
<font color="#ffff80">Are you Monsieur
Gustave of the...</font>

1104
01:16:06,396 --> 01:16:07,564
<font color="#ffff80">Yes, dammit.</font>

1105
01:16:07,772 --> 01:16:08,773
<font color="#ffff80">Confess.</font>

1106
01:16:08,982 --> 01:16:10,775
<font color="#ffff80">I'm innocent.</font>

1107
01:16:10,984 --> 01:16:12,819
<font color="#ffff80">Hmm? No, no.</font>

1108
01:16:22,328 --> 01:16:24,998
<font color="#ffff80">Forgive me, Monsieur Gustave.
I never meant to betray you.</font>

1109
01:16:25,165 --> 01:16:26,583
<font color="#ffff80">They threatened my life and now</font>

1110
01:16:26,708 --> 01:16:28,126
<font color="#ffff80">they've murdered my only family.</font>

1111
01:16:28,334 --> 01:16:29,919
<font color="#ffff80">No. Who did they kill this time?</font>

1112
01:16:30,128 --> 01:16:31,254
<font color="#ffff80">My dear sister.</font>

1113
01:16:31,379 --> 01:16:32,505
<font color="#ffff80">The girl with the club foot?</font>

1114
01:16:32,672 --> 01:16:34,090
<font color="#ffff80">Yes. Those fuckers!</font>

1115
01:16:34,299 --> 01:16:35,675
<font color="#ffff80">I tried to warn you
at the beginning.</font>

1116
01:16:35,925 --> 01:16:37,343
<font color="#ffff80">I know, darling. Let's
put that behind us.</font>

1117
01:16:37,510 --> 01:16:39,012
<font color="#ffff80">Listen, I hate to put
you on the spot,</font>

1118
01:16:39,137 --> 01:16:40,597
<font color="#ffff80">but I really must ask
you to clear my name.</font>

1119
01:16:40,805 --> 01:16:43,850
<font color="#ffff80">Obviously you're grieving...
There's more.</font>

1120
01:16:44,100 --> 01:16:45,435
<font color="#ffff80">To the story. I get it. Go on.</font>

1121
01:16:45,643 --> 01:16:47,645
<font color="#ffff80">I was the official witness
in Madame D's presence</font>

1122
01:16:47,854 --> 01:16:49,439
<font color="#ffff80">to the creation of a second will</font>

1123
01:16:49,647 --> 01:16:52,692
<font color="#ffff80">to be executed only in the
event of her death by murder.</font>

1124
01:16:52,859 --> 01:16:54,360
<font color="#ffff80">A second will? Right.</font>

1125
01:16:54,611 --> 01:16:56,154
<font color="#ffff80">In case she got bumped off?
Right.</font>

1126
01:16:56,362 --> 01:16:57,781
<font color="#ffff80">Uh-huh? But they destroyed it.</font>

1127
01:16:57,989 --> 01:16:59,449
<font color="#ffff80">Oh, dear. However...</font>

1128
01:16:59,657 --> 01:17:01,159
<font color="#ffff80">Uh-huh? I pulled a copy.</font>

1129
01:17:01,367 --> 01:17:03,495
<font color="#ffff80">A second copy of
the second will?</font>

1130
01:17:03,703 --> 01:17:04,996
<font color="#ffff80">Right. Uh-huh?</font>

1131
01:17:07,707 --> 01:17:10,043
<font color="#ffff80">What does it say? Where is it?
What's it all about, dammit?</font>

1132
01:17:10,210 --> 01:17:11,211
<font color="#ffff80">Don't keep us in suspense.</font>

1133
01:17:11,294 --> 01:17:13,004
<font color="#ffff80">This has been a complete
fucking nightmare.</font>

1134
01:17:13,213 --> 01:17:15,632
<font color="#ffff80">Just tell us what the
fuck is going on!</font>

1135
01:17:17,467 --> 01:17:18,885
<font color="#ffff80">Serge?</font>

1136
01:17:19,010 --> 01:17:20,678
<font color="#ffff80">Serge? Serge!</font>

1137
01:17:24,724 --> 01:17:27,060
<font color="#ffff80">Bloody hell. They've
strangled the poor slob.</font>

1138
01:17:55,046 --> 01:17:56,047
<font color="#ffff80">Come on! Let's go!</font>

1139
01:18:04,013 --> 01:18:05,056
<font color="#ffff80">ZERO: What do we do
if we catch him?</font>

1140
01:18:05,181 --> 01:18:06,224
<font color="#ffff80">GUSTAVE H: I don't know.</font>

1141
01:18:06,432 --> 01:18:08,726
<font color="#ffff80">He's a homicidal psychopath.
Let's stop.</font>

1142
01:18:08,935 --> 01:18:11,187
<font color="#ffff80">I can't. I can barely steer.</font>

1143
01:19:19,005 --> 01:19:22,634
<font color="#ffff80">You sick, pathetic creep.
I hate you.</font>

1144
01:19:35,355 --> 01:19:37,774
<font color="#ffff80">"'If this do be me
end, farewell!'</font>

1145
01:19:37,857 --> 01:19:39,192
<font color="#ffff80">"cried the wounded piper-boy,</font>

1146
01:19:40,777 --> 01:19:41,903
<font color="#ffff80">"whilst the muskets cracked</font>

1147
01:19:41,986 --> 01:19:43,363
<font color="#ffff80">"and the yeomen roared 'Hurrah!'</font>

1148
01:19:43,529 --> 01:19:44,697
<font color="#ffff80">"And the ramparts fell.</font>

1149
01:19:46,366 --> 01:19:49,953
<font color="#ffff80">"'Methinks me breathes me
last, me fears!' said he..."</font>

1150
01:19:50,161 --> 01:19:52,038
<font color="#ffff80">Holy shit! You got him!</font>

1151
01:19:52,288 --> 01:19:54,207
<font color="#ffff80">Well done, Zero!</font>

1152
01:20:05,385 --> 01:20:07,720
<font color="#ffff80"><i>Gustave H! You are a
fugitive from justice!</i></font>

1153
01:20:07,971 --> 01:20:10,556
<font color="#ffff80"><i>Surrender lawfully and I
will personally vouchsafe</i></font>

1154
01:20:10,848 --> 01:20:11,849
<font color="#ffff80"><i>your fair treatment.</i></font>

1155
01:20:11,975 --> 01:20:13,518
<font color="#ffff80"><i>Do not attempt to flee!</i></font>

1156
01:20:13,726 --> 01:20:15,228
<font color="#ffff80">ZERO: What do you think?
I don't know.</font>

1157
01:20:15,395 --> 01:20:16,813
<font color="#ffff80">I'd rather jump off
this cliff right now</font>

1158
01:20:16,938 --> 01:20:18,314
<font color="#ffff80">than go back to fucking prison.</font>

1159
01:20:18,523 --> 01:20:20,900
<font color="#ffff80">I say we steal that sick maniac's
motorcycle, go fetch Agatha,</font>

1160
01:20:21,150 --> 01:20:22,193
<font color="#ffff80"><i>take back Boy with Apple</i></font>

1161
01:20:22,277 --> 01:20:23,903
<font color="#ffff80">and head for the Maltese
Riviera, once and for all.</font>

1162
01:20:24,153 --> 01:20:26,906
<font color="#ffff80">Very good! You're so extraordinary, Zero.
Thank you.</font>

1163
01:20:27,073 --> 01:20:29,575
<font color="#ffff80">A moment of silence in
memoriam of a devoted servant</font>

1164
01:20:29,826 --> 01:20:32,537
<font color="#ffff80">killed violently during the
conduct of his duties.</font>

1165
01:20:35,498 --> 01:20:37,500
<font color="#ffff80">Goodbye, Serge.</font>

1166
01:20:39,002 --> 01:20:41,004
<font color="#ffff80">Okay, let's go.</font>

1167
01:20:53,808 --> 01:20:55,601
<font color="#ffff80"><i>MR. MOUSTAFA: The war
began at midnight.</i></font>

1168
01:20:55,768 --> 01:20:58,271
<font color="#ffff80"><i>Pffeifelstad fell by lunch
under heavy shelling,</i></font>

1169
01:20:58,479 --> 01:21:01,816
<font color="#ffff80"><i>and 10 battalions surged across
the long western border.</i></font>

1170
01:21:02,025 --> 01:21:03,818
<font color="#ffff80"><i>High-command advanced
to Nebelsbad.</i></font>

1171
01:21:16,039 --> 01:21:19,667
<font color="#ffff80">Compliments of <i>Herr</i> Mendl,
for the executive staff.</font>

1172
01:21:22,795 --> 01:21:25,965
<font color="#ffff80">CHUCK: General Stieglitz requests a garden-view
sitting room with an extra roll-away.</font>

1173
01:21:26,174 --> 01:21:28,134
<font color="#ffff80">Let's put him in the
Duke Leopold Suite.</font>

1174
01:21:28,343 --> 01:21:30,011
<font color="#ffff80">Secretary Woroniecki's
office cabled.</font>

1175
01:21:30,219 --> 01:21:33,806
<font color="#ffff80">He's checking in a day early.
Rooms 401 -2-3.</font>

1176
01:21:33,973 --> 01:21:35,641
<font color="#ffff80">Tell Tactical Logistics
we're moving them</font>

1177
01:21:35,808 --> 01:21:37,352
<font color="#ffff80">to a standard double
on the third floor.</font>

1178
01:21:37,560 --> 01:21:39,395
<font color="#ffff80">They'll need more
space than that.</font>

1179
01:22:02,502 --> 01:22:07,173
<font color="#ffff80">GUSTAVE H: The beginning of the end of
the end of the beginning has begun.</font>

1180
01:22:07,340 --> 01:22:10,385
<font color="#ffff80">A sad finale played off-key
on a broken-down saloon piano</font>

1181
01:22:10,593 --> 01:22:13,179
<font color="#ffff80">in the outskirts of a
forgotten ghost town.</font>

1182
01:22:13,346 --> 01:22:15,348
<font color="#ffff80">I'd rather not bear witness
to such blasphemy.</font>

1183
01:22:15,556 --> 01:22:16,557
<font color="#ffff80">Me neither.</font>

1184
01:22:16,766 --> 01:22:19,060
<font color="#ffff80">The Grand Budapest has
become a troops' barracks.</font>

1185
01:22:19,268 --> 01:22:21,729
<font color="#ffff80">I shall never cross its
threshold again in my lifetime.</font>

1186
01:22:21,938 --> 01:22:23,439
<font color="#ffff80">Me neither. Never
again shall I...</font>

1187
01:22:23,689 --> 01:22:26,692
<font color="#ffff80">Actually, I think we might be going
in there right now after all.</font>

1188
01:22:28,444 --> 01:22:29,946
<font color="#ffff80">Dmitri.</font>

1189
01:22:32,907 --> 01:22:34,617
<font color="#ffff80">Agatha.</font>

1190
01:22:45,294 --> 01:22:47,422
<font color="#ffff80">Good evening, Mr. Desgoffe und Taxis.
I'm Monsieur Chuck.</font>

1191
01:22:47,630 --> 01:22:50,883
<font color="#ffff80">We've booked you and your sisters
into the King Ferdinand Suite.</font>

1192
01:22:51,092 --> 01:22:53,052
<font color="#ffff80">Good evening. General von
Shrecker asked me...</font>

1193
01:22:53,261 --> 01:22:54,554
<font color="#ffff80">Who's that?</font>

1194
01:22:54,720 --> 01:22:56,055
<font color="#ffff80">I beg your pardon?</font>

1195
01:22:56,222 --> 01:22:58,975
<font color="#ffff80">I think that girl's got my picture.
Excuse me.</font>

1196
01:23:15,575 --> 01:23:17,577
<font color="#ffff80">AGATHA: Six. DMITRI: Hold it.</font>

1197
01:23:20,746 --> 01:23:21,789
<font color="#ffff80">DMITRI: Six.</font>

1198
01:23:24,959 --> 01:23:26,752
<font color="#ffff80">Compliments of <i>Herr</i> Mendl.</font>

1199
01:23:42,935 --> 01:23:43,936
<font color="#ffff80">GUSTAVE H: Excuse me.</font>

1200
01:23:44,103 --> 01:23:46,189
<font color="#ffff80">Have you seen a pastry girl
with a package under her arm</font>

1201
01:23:46,439 --> 01:23:47,523
<font color="#ffff80">in the last minute and a half?</font>

1202
01:23:47,773 --> 01:23:50,109
<font color="#ffff80">Yep. She just got on the elevator with Mr.
Desgoffe und Taxis.</font>

1203
01:23:50,276 --> 01:23:52,487
<font color="#ffff80">Thank you.</font>

1204
01:23:52,695 --> 01:23:54,113
<font color="#ffff80">I'm sorry. Who are you?</font>

1205
01:23:54,280 --> 01:23:55,907
<font color="#ffff80">Otto, sir, the new Lobby Boy.</font>

1206
01:23:56,032 --> 01:23:57,617
<font color="#ffff80">You haven't been
trained properly.</font>

1207
01:23:57,825 --> 01:23:59,952
<font color="#ffff80">A Lobby Boy never provides
information of that kind.</font>

1208
01:24:00,119 --> 01:24:02,121
<font color="#ffff80">You're a stone wall. Understood?</font>

1209
01:24:18,971 --> 01:24:20,556
<font color="#ffff80">Pretty picture.</font>

1210
01:24:21,390 --> 01:24:22,391
<font color="#ffff80">Sixth floor.</font>

1211
01:25:06,185 --> 01:25:07,895
<font color="#ffff80"><i>Where's Boy with Apple?</i></font>

1212
01:25:08,854 --> 01:25:11,107
<font color="#ffff80">None of your goddamn business!</font>

1213
01:25:11,899 --> 01:25:15,570
<font color="#ffff80">I'm going to blast your candy-ass
once and for all right now.</font>

1214
01:25:25,037 --> 01:25:26,581
<font color="#ffff80">Drop your weapon!</font>

1215
01:25:48,811 --> 01:25:50,730
<font color="#ffff80">Cease fire! Cease fire! Whoa!</font>

1216
01:25:50,938 --> 01:25:52,273
<font color="#ffff80">Stop it!</font>

1217
01:25:52,481 --> 01:25:54,066
<font color="#ffff80">Who's shooting who?</font>

1218
01:25:54,233 --> 01:25:56,736
<font color="#ffff80">That's Gustave H! The escaped
murderer and art thief.</font>

1219
01:25:56,944 --> 01:25:58,112
<font color="#ffff80">I've got him cornered!</font>

1220
01:25:58,321 --> 01:25:59,739
<font color="#ffff80">That's Dmitri
Desgoffe und Taxis!</font>

1221
01:25:59,947 --> 01:26:01,949
<font color="#ffff80">He's responsible for the
killing of Deputy Kovacs,</font>

1222
01:26:02,158 --> 01:26:04,994
<font color="#ffff80">Serge X and his club-footed
sister, plus his own mother!</font>

1223
01:26:06,579 --> 01:26:08,748
<font color="#ffff80">Nobody move. Everybody's
under arrest.</font>

1224
01:26:10,124 --> 01:26:12,418
<font color="#ffff80">Who's out the window?</font>

1225
01:26:12,585 --> 01:26:14,587
<font color="#ffff80">Agatha!</font>

1226
01:26:20,760 --> 01:26:21,802
<font color="#ffff80">310-bis.</font>

1227
01:26:22,011 --> 01:26:23,220
<font color="#ffff80">Hang on! Here I come!</font>

1228
01:26:48,371 --> 01:26:49,705
<font color="#ffff80">AGATHA: Something's
on the back of the...</font>

1229
01:26:56,128 --> 01:26:57,129
<font color="#ffff80">Agatha!</font>

1230
01:26:57,296 --> 01:26:59,006
<font color="#ffff80">Agatha!</font>

1231
01:26:59,215 --> 01:27:01,217
<font color="#ffff80">Are you all right? I think so.</font>

1232
01:27:02,885 --> 01:27:04,845
<font color="#ffff80">Something's on the
back of the picture.</font>

1233
01:27:18,234 --> 01:27:19,235
<font color="#ffff80"><i>MR. MOUSTAFA: She
left everything</i></font>

1234
01:27:19,318 --> 01:27:21,028
<font color="#ffff80"><i>to Monsieur Gustave, of course.</i></font>

1235
01:27:22,988 --> 01:27:25,324
<font color="#ffff80"><i>The mansion, known
as Schloss Lutz,</i></font>

1236
01:27:26,826 --> 01:27:29,912
<font color="#ffff80"><i>the factories, which produced
weapons, medicine and textiles,</i></font>

1237
01:27:32,873 --> 01:27:34,542
<font color="#ffff80"><i>an important
newspaper syndicate,</i></font>

1238
01:27:35,668 --> 01:27:38,045
<font color="#ffff80"><i>and perhaps you've
already deduced</i></font>

1239
01:27:38,379 --> 01:27:44,051
<font color="#ffff80"><i>this very institution, the
Grand Budapest Hotel.</i></font>

1240
01:27:44,385 --> 01:27:45,886
<font color="#ffff80"><i>He anointed me his successor,</i></font>

1241
01:27:46,095 --> 01:27:49,014
<font color="#ffff80"><i>and as the war continued, I
served my adopted country</i></font>

1242
01:27:49,181 --> 01:27:52,393
<font color="#ffff80"><i>from the narrow desk still found
against the wall in the next room.</i></font>

1243
01:27:53,853 --> 01:27:55,938
<font color="#ffff80"><i>He was the same
as his disciples,</i></font>

1244
01:27:56,188 --> 01:27:59,525
<font color="#ffff80"><i>insecure, vain,
superficial, blond, needy.</i></font>

1245
01:28:00,359 --> 01:28:02,570
<font color="#ffff80"><i>In the end he was even rich.</i></font>

1246
01:28:03,946 --> 01:28:07,116
<font color="#ffff80"><i>He did not succeed,
however, in growing old.</i></font>

1247
01:28:11,871 --> 01:28:13,747
<font color="#ffff80">"Dearly beloved, we are
gathered together..."</font>

1248
01:28:13,956 --> 01:28:15,791
<font color="#ffff80"><i>MR. MOUSTAFA: Nor did
my darling Agatha.</i></font>

1249
01:28:16,041 --> 01:28:18,294
<font color="#ffff80"><i>She and our infant son would
be killed two years later</i></font>

1250
01:28:18,544 --> 01:28:21,380
<font color="#ffff80"><i>by the Prussian grippe.
An absurd little disease.</i></font>

1251
01:28:21,589 --> 01:28:24,133
<font color="#ffff80"><i>Today we treat it
in</i> a <i>single</i> week,</font>

1252
01:28:24,258 --> 01:28:26,802
<font color="#ffff80"><i>but, in those days
many millions died.</i></font>

1253
01:28:30,097 --> 01:28:31,932
<font color="#ffff80"><i>On the 21st day of
the occupation,</i></font>

1254
01:28:32,141 --> 01:28:34,894
<font color="#ffff80"><i>the morning the independent
state of Zubrowka</i></font>

1255
01:28:35,060 --> 01:28:36,228
<font color="#ffff80"><i>officially ceased to exist,</i></font>

1256
01:28:36,395 --> 01:28:38,397
<font color="#ffff80"><i>we traveled with Monsieur
Gustave to Lutz.</i></font>

1257
01:28:38,564 --> 01:28:40,816
<font color="#ffff80">In answer to your earlier
question, by the way,</font>

1258
01:28:41,066 --> 01:28:42,902
<font color="#ffff80">of course.</font>

1259
01:28:44,737 --> 01:28:47,573
<font color="#ffff80">Zero asked me about my humble
beginnings in the hotel trade.</font>

1260
01:28:47,740 --> 01:28:50,075
<font color="#ffff80">I was, perhaps, for a time,
considered the best Lobby Boy</font>

1261
01:28:50,284 --> 01:28:52,661
<font color="#ffff80">we'd ever had at the
Grand Budapest.</font>

1262
01:28:52,912 --> 01:28:54,330
<font color="#ffff80">I think I can say that.</font>

1263
01:28:54,580 --> 01:28:56,415
<font color="#ffff80">This one finally surpassed me.</font>

1264
01:28:56,624 --> 01:28:59,585
<font color="#ffff80">Although, I must say, he had
an exceptional teacher.</font>

1265
01:28:59,752 --> 01:29:00,920
<font color="#ffff80">Truly.</font>

1266
01:29:06,175 --> 01:29:09,136
<font color="#ffff80">"Whence came these two
radiant, celestial brothers,</font>

1267
01:29:09,345 --> 01:29:10,638
<font color="#ffff80">"united, for an instant,</font>

1268
01:29:10,846 --> 01:29:15,100
<font color="#ffff80">"as they crossed the stratosphere
of our starry window?</font>

1269
01:29:15,309 --> 01:29:18,103
<font color="#ffff80">"One from the East and
one from the West."</font>

1270
01:29:18,270 --> 01:29:20,022
<font color="#ffff80">Very good.</font>

1271
01:29:20,272 --> 01:29:22,274
<font color="#ffff80">Don't flirt with her.</font>

1272
01:29:24,610 --> 01:29:26,862
<font color="#ffff80">Why are we stopping at
a barley field again?</font>

1273
01:29:35,204 --> 01:29:38,332
<font color="#ffff80">I find these black
uniforms very drab.</font>

1274
01:29:42,836 --> 01:29:44,129
<font color="#ffff80">Well, hello there, chaps.</font>

1275
01:29:44,213 --> 01:29:45,798
<font color="#ffff80">We were just talking about you.</font>

1276
01:29:46,048 --> 01:29:47,841
<font color="#ffff80">Documents, please.</font>

1277
01:29:47,967 --> 01:29:49,802
<font color="#ffff80">With pleasure, as always.</font>

1278
01:29:54,223 --> 01:29:56,016
<font color="#ffff80">You're the first of the
official death squads</font>

1279
01:29:56,225 --> 01:29:58,477
<font color="#ffff80">to whom we've been
formally introduced.</font>

1280
01:29:58,644 --> 01:30:00,646
<font color="#ffff80">How do you do?</font>

1281
01:30:01,855 --> 01:30:03,899
<font color="#ffff80"><i>Plus</i> ça change, am I right?</font>

1282
01:30:08,362 --> 01:30:11,740
<font color="#ffff80">Uh, that's a migratory visa with
stage three worker status, darling.</font>

1283
01:30:11,991 --> 01:30:12,992
<font color="#ffff80">Read this.</font>

1284
01:30:22,334 --> 01:30:23,669
<font color="#ffff80">SOLDIER: Come outside.</font>

1285
01:30:23,836 --> 01:30:25,170
<font color="#ffff80">GUSTAVE H: Now, stay there.</font>

1286
01:30:27,381 --> 01:30:29,675
<font color="#ffff80">I give you my word, if you
lay a finger on this man,</font>

1287
01:30:29,883 --> 01:30:32,052
<font color="#ffff80">I'll see you
dishonorably discharged,</font>

1288
01:30:32,261 --> 01:30:35,347
<font color="#ffff80">locked up in the stockade
and hanged by sundown.</font>

1289
01:30:36,682 --> 01:30:38,517
<font color="#ffff80"><i>MR. MOUSTAFA: There are still
faint glimmers of civilization</i></font>

1290
01:30:38,684 --> 01:30:40,853
<font color="#ffff80"><i>left in this barbaric
slaughterhouse</i></font>

1291
01:30:40,978 --> 01:30:43,063
<font color="#ffff80"><i>that was once known as humanity.</i></font>

1292
01:30:46,400 --> 01:30:49,737
<font color="#ffff80">You filthy, goddamn,
pock-marked, fascist assholes!</font>

1293
01:30:50,863 --> 01:30:53,532
<font color="#ffff80">MR. MOUSTAFA: He
was one of them.</font>

1294
01:30:53,741 --> 01:30:55,659
<font color="#ffff80"><i>What more is there to say?</i></font>

1295
01:31:03,417 --> 01:31:06,045
<font color="#ffff80">What happened in the end?</font>

1296
01:31:06,253 --> 01:31:08,255
<font color="#ffff80">In the end they shot him.</font>

1297
01:31:10,049 --> 01:31:12,051
<font color="#ffff80">So it all went to me.</font>

1298
01:31:20,893 --> 01:31:24,146
<font color="#ffff80"><i>YOUNG</i> WRITER: <i>After dinner, we went
to collect the keys to our rooms,</i></font>

1299
01:31:24,396 --> 01:31:26,231
<font color="#ffff80"><i>but Monsieur Jean had
abandoned his post.</i></font>

1300
01:31:26,398 --> 01:31:28,567
<font color="#ffff80">I expect he's forgotten
all about us.</font>

1301
01:31:28,776 --> 01:31:29,902
<font color="#ffff80">YOUNG WRITER: In recent
years, of course,</font>

1302
01:31:30,069 --> 01:31:32,321
<font color="#ffff80"><i>such properties and holdings
as the Grand Budapest</i></font>

1303
01:31:32,571 --> 01:31:36,158
<font color="#ffff80"><i>had with very few exceptions
become common property.</i></font>

1304
01:31:37,117 --> 01:31:39,161
<font color="#ffff80"><i>While the precise terms
of his negotiation</i></font>

1305
01:31:39,411 --> 01:31:41,288
<font color="#ffff80"><i>with the new government
had never been announced,</i></font>

1306
01:31:41,497 --> 01:31:42,664
<font color="#ffff80"><i>the result was an open secret,</i></font>

1307
01:31:43,582 --> 01:31:46,293
<font color="#ffff80"><i>Zero Moustafa had traded a
great and important fortune</i></font>

1308
01:31:46,502 --> 01:31:50,798
<font color="#ffff80"><i>in exchange for one costly,
unprofitable, doomed hotel.</i></font>

1309
01:31:51,840 --> 01:31:52,841
<font color="#ffff80"><i>Why?</i></font>

1310
01:31:53,092 --> 01:31:55,135
<font color="#ffff80"><i>Was it merely sentimental?</i></font>

1311
01:31:55,344 --> 01:31:59,098
<font color="#ffff80"><i>It was quite forward of me
and a bit out of character,</i></font>

1312
01:31:59,264 --> 01:32:01,100
<font color="#ffff80"><i>but I felt I must know,</i></font>

1313
01:32:01,350 --> 01:32:03,352
<font color="#ffff80"><i>for my health, I suppose.</i></font>

1314
01:32:05,938 --> 01:32:08,148
<font color="#ffff80">Forgive me for asking. I
hope I haven't upset you.</font>

1315
